title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Sift and set aside.

title: diet  chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Put chicken in shallow pan and pour sauce over.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Add the mushrooms and cheese to each chicken breast. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: lima bean patties
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Make into balls and roll in fine crumbs and heat in oven as croquettes at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes on sprayed cookie sheet, turning them over after 30 minutes or fry as patties.
Serve with your favorite sauce.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large pan heat oil.
Dice onions and add to hot oil, cook until clear.
Cut potatoes into bite-size pieces.
Add potatoes slowly to oil, browning them.
After all the potatoes are browned, add tomato sauce, parsley, salt and pepper.
Bring to the boil then reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are soft.
Add cheese and simmer another 15 minutes.
Good served with bread and butter.
Freezes well.

title: creamy vegetable ham soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add broth, milk and Velveeta.
Stir until melted.
Stir in vegetables, ham, salt and pepper.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Chill before serving.

title: salsa mix
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended.

title: smoothest southern pound cake
directions: Beat softened butter at medium speed with mixer about 2 minutes, until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: pam's pleasurable nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning (no water) and stir thoroughly.
In a large sauce pan melt cheese over medium heat until fully melted.
Add ground beef, salsa and can of tomatoes and chilies to cheese.
Stir until all is heated.
Serve hot over Tostitos, chips or use as a dip.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bottom Layer:
Melt 1 stick butter; add 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Press in bottom of pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice.
Place in large casserole dish.
Mix soup with 1 can of milk. Add onion, salt and pepper to taste. Pour over potatoes.
Cover with foil or lid. Bake at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 8.

title: bread sticks
directions: Butter both sides of bread; cut into sticks.
Put on cookie sheet and bake in slow oven at 325° until golden brown and toasted, about 15 or 20 minutes.
Can use any kind of bread. Keeps well in Tupperware.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add boiling water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve jello in hot liquid and cool.
Gently stir in the ginger ale.
Chill until partially set.

title: butterscotch spiders
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Pour over noodles in bowl, coating well.
Spoon on waxed paper and chill until firm.

title: crab meat mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Put the soup, mayonnaise, cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce into saucepan over low heat.
(Or use double boiler.)
Stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add onion, celery and crab meat.
Pour into greased mold and chill overnight. Unmold onto a dish or tray.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Combine ingredients in order given; mix well.
Spread batter in a greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: cherry bread
directions: Melt butter in dish you will bake in at 350°.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl and pour butter in.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into butter greased dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until done.
Cut in squares after cool.

title: marsala wine custard
directions: Combine beaten egg yolks with sugar and wine.
Beat with a rotary beater until well blended.
Place the mixture in the top of a double boiler over warm water.
Beat with a rotary beater until well blended.

title: chicken francaise(2 servings)
directions: Season the flattened chicken breast lightly with salt and pepper, if desired.

title: lemon brownies
directions: Cream together the butter, powdered sugar and flour and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 300° to 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until looks dry but not brown.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar, flour and lemon juice.
Pour over the baked crust and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until light. Gradually beat in lemon, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Add sour cream.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add heavy cream.
Pour into spring-side pan.
Place this in a large pan with water.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large heavy skillet, add bell pepper, onion and oleo.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Next, add in the flour by sprinkling over the contents of the entire skillet.
Stir the contents until the flour is blended well with rest of ingredients.
Now add the soup and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Slice all 3 of the hard boiled eggs, but only add 2 of them to the skillet; leave one for garnish.
Add cooked ham chunks next and bring contents to boil and then remove from heat.
Pour skillet's contents into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange the biscuits on top of the mixture. Add remaining egg slices on top of this and bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until the biscuits are brown.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake yellow cake as directed on box.
After removing cake from oven (immediately, while the cake is hot), use a fork to make about 12 fork holes in cake.
Pour can of crushed pineapple (with juice) on top of cake.
Allow cake to cool for about 2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Start in cold oven.

title: orange carrots
directions: Wash and peel carrots.
Cook in a small amount of boiling salted water until tender.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually add orange juice and lemon juice.
Add to melted butter and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour sauce over carrots.
Serves 4.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Put beans and water in large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add all the ingredients, except the tomato sauce and brown sugar.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until beans are tender.
Add the tomato sauce and brown sugar.
Bring the soup back to a boil for a few minutes and it is ready to eat.

title: banana salad
directions: Cream sugars and egg; add flour.
Add milk.
Heat over medium heat and boil 1 to 2 minutes until thick; cool.
Layer sliced bananas.
Top with pudding.
Repeat.
Top with chopped peanuts. Makes 6 servings.

title: applesauce layer cake(early 1900 recipe)
directions: Dissolve soda in applesauce.
Cream lard and sugar.
Add applesauce.
Cream together, then add dry ingredients.
Bake in layer pans in moderate oven about 45 minutes (325° works good).

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into loaf on shallow baking pan lined with aluminum foil.
Spread 3 tablespoons catsup on top before baking.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese log
directions: Note:
Have ingredients at room temperature and mix well.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and paprika together. Add corn and beaten egg yolks. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Shape into patties. Fry in hot grease until browned on both sides.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Cook two minutes longer.
Remove from heat.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
After mixing, add 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Fill into 2 baked pie shells and refrigerate overnight or until well set.

title: taco bake
directions: Mix taco seasoning mix with beef; add picante sauce (or tomato paste).
Place in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with corn, then cheese.
Mix cornbread meal according to directions on package. Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cornbread mix is done.

title: chicken and rice marsilla
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Pour rice and bouillon in bottom.
Place cut up chicken on top and then spread cream of mushroom soup on top of chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top. Cover and seal aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.
This recipe also works well in the crock-pot.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine tuna, bread crumbs, celery and onion.
Blend mayonnaise, chili sauce and lemon juice.
Form into 4 patties. Fry in lightly oiled skillet over medium heat for about 5 minutes or until browned.
Serve on toasted hamburger rolls with lettuce and sliced tomatoes.

title: crackle top ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Stir in molasses.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine with molasses mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll dough in small balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° about 18 to 20 minutes. Yield:
8 dozen.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix together in heavy saucepan. Heat until butter and sugar have melted. Cool and use. Makes 15 ounces.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of vegetable oil.
Remove and saute peppers and onion.
Remove and make gravy with oil, flour and water (or milk).
Cook 2 cups rice and set aside.
Layer in casserole the chops, onions, green peppers, rice with gravy and tomato juice, beginning with rice and ending with gravy, rice and tomato juice.
Salt and pepper as needed.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: cherry-cherry cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare the white cake as per ingredients and directions on box.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake as directed on box.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Make holes in cake 1-inch apart and 1-inch deep.
Mix the cherry jello in 1 cup boiling water until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water and mix well.
Pour jello into holes in cake.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread the can of cherry pie filling over cake evenly.
Cover with whipped topping.
Serve.

title: peach preserves
directions: Peel and wash peaches.
Cut peaches in slices and cut out seed. Put peaches in boiler and cover with water.
Put on stove; bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes or when peaches look tender (the longer the peaches boil the tougher they get).
Turn down on low heat and mash up the peaches while covered with water (use potato masher) until chopped well.
Pour 5 pounds sugar in boiler and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring back to a boil on high heat to make syrup for preserves.
Be sure not to let boil over.
Cut heat down to low to keep preserves from burning.
Be sure and stir often.
Be sure everything is grease free.
When peach preserves are ready, place in pint jars and turn upside down to cool.
Will need approximately 6 to 12 jars, depending on how many peaches are in the basket.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine
morsels, margarine and corn syrup in saucepan. Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir
in vanilla and sugar.	Add Rice Krispies, mixing lightly until well coated.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan,
melt margarine. Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, then water.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add cocoa mixture, beating well.
Stir in 1/2 cup Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until cake springs back.

title: chocolate peanut butter drops
directions: Cream peanut butter, shortening and sugar together well; beat in egg.
Sift flour with soda, salt and spices; add to egg mixture with the water.
Mix thoroughly, then stir in oatmeal and chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for about 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.
While still warm, sprinkle with sugar lightly (optional).
These are very good keepers.

title: spicy apple cookies
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Stir in apples, walnuts, raisins and butterscotch pieces.
Combine brown sugar and margarine.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs and apple juice to sugar-margarine mixture.
Beat until blended.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute the onion in butter.
Stir in flour, seasoned salt and seasoned pepper. Gradually add the milk, stirring constantly. Arrange a layer of carrots in a 2-quart casserole.
Place 3 slices of cheese over the carrots.
Repeat layers.
Pour the sauce over the carrots and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: yummy fudge pie
directions: In saucepan heat margarine and chocolate until melted; blend well.
Beat in sugar, eggs and milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Turn mixture into prepared pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let cool.
Good with whipped topping.

title: lemon snow pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin, 1/2 cup of the sugar and 1/4 cup of the water in medium saucepan.
(I use the microwave.)
Blend in egg yolks and remaining water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.

title: canned garden salad
directions: Put all vegetables into a large bowl and toss together. Boil together the sugar, olive oil, pepper, vinegar and salt and pour dressing over the vegetables; toss all together and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Alternately add flour and milk, beating after each addition.
Stir in coconut.
Spoon into greased 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in casserole.
Cut chicken into chunks and place on top of broccoli.
Mix the cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour this over the broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: upside down pizza
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain.
Add pizza sauce.
Put in a 9 X 13 pan.
Cover with cheeses.
Blot on sour cream.
Lay rolls on top. Butter the rolls.
Cover with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350 for 25 - 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and canned pumpkin, then add sugar, brown sugar, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Thoroughly blend in evaporated milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell(s) and bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Lower temperature to 325° and bake for 40 to 45 more minutes, or until knife blade comes out clean when inserted into center of the pie.

title: hot weather beverage
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Freeze to a slush.

title: chicken with lemon
directions: Salt and pepper chicken as desired.
Dredge chicken in flour. Heat oil and butter and brown chicken.
Remove.
In remaining fat, cook onions and mushrooms until onions are translucent.
Add 3 tablespoons of remaining flour and seasonings.
Stir.
Combine liquid ingredients and add to contents of casserole.
Over high heat, cook, stirring, until sauce thickens.
Replace chicken. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Bake the rice and chicken with boiling water at 325° in covered dish for 2 hours.
Add soup and milk.
Put back in oven for 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: extraordinary chocolate brownies
directions: Mix dressing, eggs and water until well blended.
Stir in brownie mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until edges pull away from pan.
Top with bars; let stand 5 minutes until melted.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes and those listed for topping, with electric mixer until well blended.
Place hash browns in 4-quart casserole dish; pour cheese mixture over hash browns.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter allotted for topping over bread crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour milk over all the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in 1-inch squares.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Bring 1 cup liquid from canned pears to a boil.
Dissolve jello into hot liquid.
At this point, add gelatine to keep mold firm by dissolving 1 teaspoon Knox gelatine into 2 to 3 teaspoons cold water, then add to jello.
Soften cream cheese; add 2 teaspoons cream and beat to creamy consistency.
When jello is cool, beat in cheese until cheese is fully dissolved in jello. Set in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Add drained and mashed pears (dicing works best).
Fold in whipped cream; pour into mold and refrigerate.
Remove from mold following mold's instructions.

title: french toast
directions: Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Add cinnamon to egg mixture. Dip each side of bread in mixture.
Brown on both sides.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover the mixture with 2 cups of crushed potato chips or use corn flakes if you don't want that much salt and grease.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until hot through.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: almond rice
directions: Cook rice and drain.
Mix rice with soup and butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Add toasted almonds to the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: basil bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Generously butter a 7 or 8 x 3-inch round pan; set aside.
Combine flour, baking soda, basil, salt and pepper in a large bowl of electric mixer fitted with a dough hook. Mix at medium speed several seconds just to blend.
Form a well in the center of the mixture; pour in melted butter.
With mixer at medium speed, slowly pour in buttermilk and blend, stopping once or twice to scrape down sides of bowl.
Continue mixing until dough comes away from the sides of the bowl and wraps around hook (about 10 minutes), Dough will be quite soft.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cut up onions, peppers and celery; saute in fat.
Add tomatoes and paste.
Let simmer 40 minutes.
Before serving, add shrimp. Serve over rice.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in coconut, dates, walnuts and vanilla. Mix.
Bake in greased casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out and stir immediately with a wooden spoon.
Let cool. Form into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Makes 30 balls.
Keep in airtight container.

title: broccoli and bow ties
directions: Cook the broccoli for 3 minutes in a large pot of boiling salted water.
Remove the broccoli from the water with a slotted spoon or sieve.
Place in a large bowl and set aside.
In the same water, cook the bow tie pasta according to the package directions, about 12 minutes.
Drain well and add to the broccoli.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In skillet, fry beef cubes until slightly brown.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low temperature for 4 to 6 hours.

title: grandma nelson's caboose soup
directions: Slice sausage thinly.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Add peas and 1 cup of water.
Cook until potatoes are soft and then add milk. Season with pepper.

title: chocolate cake(22 minute cake)
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large bowl.
Bring to a boil the water, oleo, shortening and cocoa; pour over flour mixture. Combine remaining ingredients, add to batter and blend well.
(Mix with a spoon.
Do not use mixer.)
Pour batter into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes.

title: our best ever brownies
directions: Double batch to make one 9 x 12-inch cake pan.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add green peppers and onion and cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer half the noodles, meat sauce and Velveeta.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and bake in oven at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave spaghetti sauce
directions: Place ground beef in a 3-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until beef is cooked through, stirring twice; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave, covered, on High for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave, uncovered, on Medium-high for 1 hour, stirring twice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: plain flour biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450° to 500°.
Grease pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk slowly; mix to smooth consistency.
Knead dough gently on floured surface.
Do not overknead.
Use hand to press out dough to 1/2 to 1-inch thickness.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Coat both sides of biscuit with melted butter.
Bake for about 10 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: marvelous macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Add almonds and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto a lightly greased baking sheet. Garnish with candied cherry halves, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, until edges are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In 1-quart shallow casserole, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
In medium bowl, mix remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into crust comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and evaporated milk in blender.
In large bowl, add egg mixture to sweetened condensed milk, Cool Whip and milk; whip until smooth.
Add salt, vanilla and peaches.
Stir. Pour into can and add milk to fill line if not full.
Freeze according to churn instructions.
(Other fruits may be used or add extra vanilla for vanilla ice cream.)

title: princess brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed.
Mix the cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend well.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add Bisquick, grated cheese, oil, salt and pepper to eggs, then add zucchini and onions.
Mix well.
Grease bottom of large baking pan with butter. Pour zucchini mixture.
Bake for another 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars, then add eggs and vanilla. Mix together.
Add flour, blended oatmeal, salt, baking powder, baking soda and mix in with other ingredients.
Mix in rest of ingredients and stir with spoon by hand.
Put on cookie sheet in shape of golf ball and push down.

title: peach jello
directions: Drain peaches. Save juice. Soften cream cheese and mix with peaches until smooth. Heat peach juice until boiling. Dissolve jello in juice. Blend well. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into mold or oblong casserole. Refrigerate 6 hours.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and lightly grease a 2 quart baking dish.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat, stir and cook ground beef, onion and celery until juices run clear. Drain.
Pour mixture into baking dish with vegetable soup and thyme; stir well. Spread mashed potatoes on top.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more, or until cheese has melted.

title: spinach salad
directions: Rinse in very hot water and cool quickly to make crisp.

title: rosemary's chicken divan
directions: Layer chicken breast and broccoli in baking dish.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(You may also top with bread crumbs.)

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar with cornstarch.
Stir in cherry juice. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Add remaining sugar, cherries, butter and food coloring.
(Mixture will be very thick.) Let stand while preparing pastry.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry; fill.
Adjust lattice top.
Crimp edge high.
Bake at 400° for 55 minutes.

title: louisiana beans and rice
directions: Brown meat.
Don't pour off drippings.
Add other ingredients. Stir until well mixed. Cover, simmer 30 minutes until rice is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.
Good fall and winter dish.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 2 pie plates.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
(No crust needed; makes own.) Serves 6 to 8 per pie.
Makes 2 pies.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions about 5 minutes, drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and stir in carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onion. Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread 1/2 the stuffing mix in bottom of 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable and soup mixture over this.
Sprinkle the remaining stuffing mix over the vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
(You may find you only need half of the 8 ounce stuffing mix.)

title: banana cream pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Add a layer of bananas on cooled pie crust before adding filling.
Bake pie shell.
Stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Blend milk and egg yolks.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Immediately pour into baked pie shell.
Cool for 2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze water out of defrosted spinach.
Mix spinach with all other ingredients; do not use blender.
Mixture will be lumpy. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: easy cutouts
directions: Mix thoroughly in order given. Chill for 1 hour. Roll dough on lightly floured board and cut with your favorite cookie cutters. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: dill meat - fricassee
directions: Take lamb on the bone; e.g., from the shoulder or back.
If necessary, rinse the meat under cold running water.
Place it in a saucepan.
Measure enough water to cover the meat.
Add 2 teaspoons salt per 1 quart of water.
Bring to a boil.
Skim off thoroughly.
Add peppercorns, carrot and leek.
Cover the saucepan and let the meat simmer over a low heat until tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Strain the liquid.
Keep the meat hot.
Make the gravy.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes or until done.

title: fruit and nut summer slaw
directions: Drain oranges, reserving syrup.
In a serving bowl, mix together oranges, cabbage, celery and raisins.

Slice banana and dice apple; combine with mandarin orange syrup and lemon juice. Pour over banana and apple, stirring to coat to prevent darkening. Then, with a slotted spoon, remove fruit and add to slaw along with nuts.
Combine 2 tablespoons of the juice mixture with yogurt and salt.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over salad and mix gently. Sprinkle with poppy seed.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine hot water, salt, shortening and sugar in bowl large enough to allow for some rising during storage.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast softened in the lukewarm water.
Add the egg and half the flour and beat well.
Stir in more of the flour, enough to make a dough easily handled.
Grease top of dough.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Cut off dough as needed.
Shape into biscuits and place side by side in a greased or oiled pan. Cover with a clean towel and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove; brush with melted butter.
Makes about 18 medium size rolls.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: In a casserole dish, melt margarine on bottom.
Layer pan with potatoes, then cheeses and then ham.
Sprinkle flour over top with some onions, salt and pepper.
Continue layers with potatoes, then cheese, ham, flour, salt, pepper and onions.
Pour hot milk over top.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven, stir, then return to oven for another 40 minutes.
Let sit for 20 minutes.

title: rolls with whole wheat
directions: Combine yeast, warm water, egg,
sugar and oil.
Stir in whole wheat flour until
well
blended.
Sift
together
flour, baking powder, soda and
salt.
Stir
into
other
ingredients. Knead for few minutes on
floured board.
Roll out about 1-inch thick.
Cut into 2 to 3-inch round disks.
Place in muffin tins or large baking dish.
Let rise
covered
with
cloth in a warm place for about 2 hours.
Bake
to 20 minutes at 400°.
Cut disks can be frozen on greased sheet until hard and then bagged in freezer until needed.
Remove
only
amount wanted.
Thawed, allow to rise and bake.

title: scalloped cornbread corn
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Pour into a casserole dish with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and celery in oil for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except spaghetti.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mix with cooked spaghetti.

title: fresh fruit topping
directions: Beat cream cheese and marshmallow cream together.
Add enough pineapple juice to make the mixture a nice consistency.
Blend well.
Put in a bowl and serve over melon balls or fresh fruit assortment.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Let sit for 2 hours or more for better flavor.
Serves 6 plus.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Drop on cookie sheet that has been greased. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mush
directions: Heat water to a boil.
Mix corn meal, salt and 1 cup cold water.
Stir into boiling water.
Cook 30 minutes.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
When cool, slice and fry.

title: daddy's corn bread
directions: In our family, Daddy always made the corn bread and at almost 80, he still does.
He always used his well-seasoned cast-iron corn stick pans or sometimes his equally seasoned black iron skillet. Getting the shortening "smokin hot" is the key to a crispy brown outside.
If you really want to be southern, substitute bacon grease for the shortening.
You may also use white corn meal instead of yellow for a more cake-like texture or replace the white flour with whole wheat if your preference is a coarse corn bread. Any way is delicious!

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook 1/4 cup chopped onion and butter until tender.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish mix onion, chicken broth, chunk chicken, rice and cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green bean salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and salt to boiling point.
Set aside to cool.
Drain beans and other ingredients.
Add vegetables.
Pour vinegar mixture over ingredients on front.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Place in loaf pan with bacon on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. You may substitute bacon by spreading 2 tablespoons salad oil over top. Serves 4.

title: cape cod cranberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Blend in cranberry sauce, pineapple (or Mandarin oranges, cut up), nuts and wine.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish; refrigerate until set.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in dish, stir in remaining ingredients until lumps are gone.
Dump fruit on top.
Do not stir!!	Bake one hour at 350 degrees.

title: zucchini saute
directions: In a 10-inch pan, melt butter/margarine over medium heat.
Stir in zucchini, onion and basil.
Toss to coat all vegetables evenly. Cook, stirring occasionally until zucchini is almost tender-crisp, about 8 minutes.
Stir in tomato cubes; cook 1 minute.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Cover and let stand for a minute or so until cheeses begin to melt.
Serves 6.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: First, boil the chicken.
Take out and let cool.
Take all fat off of the chicken.
Use the broth to cook the rice in.
Add soup.

title: kapusta(polish sauerkraut with spareribs)
directions: Put spareribs in a large Dutch oven or soup pot.
Cover with water; add bay leaves and garlic.
Boil and simmer 1 hour.
Wash sauerkraut well.
Drain some of water off the ribs (most of it) and put sauerkraut in with ribs and remaining water.
Add 1 chopped onion and the mushrooms.
Let simmer all day (at least 3 to 4 hours).
Add bacon, flour and potatoes and let simmer about 1 hour longer.
Polish sausage may also be added at this time.

title: holland house cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flavoring and dry ingredients. Roll dough into small balls, smaller than a walnut.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: date goodies
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook in saucepan 5 to 7 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool for 1/2 hour.
Add Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon into bowl of coconut.
Roll in balls.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Wash and scrape celery; cut into very small pieces. Add water and cook until very soft and tender; rub through sieve. Heat milk in double boiler; add milk to celery. Melt butter; add flour and seasoning. Add soup, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: soft-boiled egg sandwich
directions: Toast muffin; butter and cheese like a grilled sandwich.
Poach egg in sauce.
Remove when soft-boiled and place on bun with a tablespoon of sauce.
Break yolk and serve to waiting parasites. This is an ideal brunch for late visiting guest on holiday mornings, when you have already been cooking for 2 hours.
Makes 1 serving.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll like salami.
(Makes 4 rolls about the size of Ritz crackers.)
Wrap in foil and seal ends. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove foil; place rolls on rack in pan. (Bake on rack so excess fat can drain off.)
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
When done, roll in paper towel to absorb excess fat.
Cool and rewrap in foil.
Keep refrigerated.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in order.
Form into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Do not bake.

title: velveeta, tomatoes and peppers
directions: Spray 8 x 10-inch oblong Pyrex dish with nonstick spray. Slice tomato/tomatoes and layer in dish.
Top with banana peppers and more tomatoes, if desired.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of parsley over layers of tomatoes and peppers.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave on High, 6 to 8 minutes or until tomatoes and peppers are done.
Remove from oven and top with Velveeta cheese and cover again until cheese melts.

title: mock champagne cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box; pour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake according to directions on box. Let cool, then punch holes in top with fork or ice pick; set aside.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place half the artichoke hearts in food processor and chop coarsely.
Add half the Parmesan cheese, cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed and garlic.
Process until smooth. Scrape mixture into a 10-inch pie plate.
Repeat procedure with remaining half of ingredients, adding to pie plate after processing.
Smooth top with spatula.
Bake until hot and bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately with crackers or bread sticks.

title: corn salad relish
directions: Mix together and cook 20 minutes.
Seal while hot.

title: salmon loaf with egg sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a loaf.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and flour the chicken.
Beat 1 egg and dip chicken into it, then the dry mixture again.
Put into a greased pan, pour 1 stick melted butter over chicken and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy apple syrup
directions: Bring to boil, stirring constantly.

title: pear nog(4 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Serve immediately.
If served later, stir.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat chicken and dip in flour. Dip in eggs. Roll in bread crumbs. Pan-fry until done.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix well and put in 4-quart ice cream freezer.

title: noodle bake
directions: Melt butter in skillet; brown ground beef and drain.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes. Cook noodles and drain.
Add green onions, cream cheese (cut in cubes) and sour cream.
In casserole, make a layer of meat sauce; top with a layer of noodles.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream vegetable oil, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour with baking powder and add alternately with the sour cream to the mixture.
Stir in flavoring well and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in a tube pan.

title: microwave chewy graham-coconut bars
directions: Cook in slices in microwave for 10 to 12 minutes. Top with Prego spaghetti sauce.
Heat in microwave 2 to 3 minutes. Proverbs 3:10.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Add cereal and shape into small balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture with toothpick. Place on waxed paper.

title: easy vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into ice cream freezer. Mix until it is hard to turn. Make sure to add rock salt.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Crumble chicken into greased pan.
Mix soup with broth.
Heat until mixed good.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix flour, buttermilk and butter.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Then pour flour mixture over and cook in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
To make sauce, melt butter in saucepan. Add flour and stir.
Remove from heat.
Add mustard, Worcestershire, salt and cayenne pepper.
Add milk.
Put over medium heat, stirring constantly until bubbling and thick.
Add sour cream and 1 cup of cheese to sauce.
Stir until blended.
In an 8-inch square pan, layer 1/2 macaroni, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: peanut banana grahams
directions: In a medium bowl combine bananas and peanut butter.
Mix well. Spread 2 tablespoons of mixture onto a graham cracker square.
Top with another graham cracker square.
Wrap in foil and freeze. Makes 26.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in 2-quart pan.
Cook until it will form 2 or 3-inch thread.
Pour in peanuts.
Cook until light brown in color, stirring constantly.
Add soda; stir rapidly. Pour on lightly buttered plate.
Cool.
Break in pieces.

title: smoked turkey sausage en croute
directions: Separate crescent roll dough into two long rectangles.
Press to seal perforations.
Spread each piece of dough lightly with mustard.
Cut sausage in half crosswise.
Place each half on a dough rectangle.
Carefully pull pastry over sausage and pinch to seal. Trim any extra dough at ends.
Place sausage seam side down on ungreased baking pan.
Decorate with any remaining dough. Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Serve warm.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Simmer potatoes, onion and celery in 1 1/2 cups water in a covered 2-quart saucepan.
Do not drain.
Combine Watkins cream soup mix and flour.
Add milk and remaining 1 1/2 cups water.
Add this mixture slowly to the vegetables while stirring and bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally to prevent scorching.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.
Very good!

title: coffee toffee torte
directions: Oil an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Crush 1/2 of the macaroons and spread in bottom of pan.
Slightly soften almond ice cream and spread on top of crumbs.
Drizzle 4 tablespoons fudge sauce over top.
Crush remaining macaroons and spread on top of ice cream. Soften coffee ice cream and spread over second layer of crumbs. Drizzle with 4 more tablespoons of fudge sauce.
Freeze.
Crush Heath bars and sprinkle on top.
Freeze for 4 to 5 hours.
Remove torte from pan and place on a serving platter.
Let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Pass fudge sauce and whipped cream when ready to serve.

title: chicken pot pie family style
directions: In a saucepot melt 4 tablespoons butter with onion.
Add 1/2 cup flour; cook.
Do not let brown.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly until smooth and thick.
Add vegetables, chicken and spices.
Pour into a 2-quart glass baking dish.
In a medium bowl, stir remaining flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 1 tablespoon butter until mix is crumbly.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add milk. Add flour to mix and stir.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Spread over chicken mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant meat into bite-size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Cut vegetables into cubes (another 2 months).
Place meat in a pan and cover with 1,000 gallons of brown gravy and simmer for 4 weeks.
Garnish with parsley.
Will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, add 2 rabbits.
This is not recommended, as very few people like hare in their stew.

title: caraway cheese muffins
directions: Stif flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add egg mix to flour mix.
Combine cheese and caraway seed, fold into batter.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: herb cheese wedges
directions: Combine Bisquick, onion, sugar and herbs.
Mix the egg and milk together; beat slightly.
Add this, the butter and wine to the dry ingredients.
Beat until blended.

title: baked cheese dip
directions: Cut dried beef in small pieces. mix all ingredients together. Cut the middle out of the round loaf of Hawaiian bread. Put the mixture in the middle of the bread, wrap in foil and
bake at 325 degrees for 1 hr.
Serve with Ritz crackers. When the dip is almost gone, cut the bread into pieces and dot the remainder of the dip on it.

title: little buckaroo snacks
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in an airtight container. Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together except save 1/2 package of beef to roll ball in. Chill.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool and serve.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Put in blender the sugar, tomato soup, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, oil, salt and pepper.
Cook carrots in boiling water 5 minutes (no longer).
Put in ice water to cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.

title: tasty toss up
directions: Cook pasta; drain and cool.
In large bowl, combine pasta, tuna, cucumbers, tomato, celery, green peppers and onions.
In a small bowl, blend together dressing, mayonnaise, mustard and seasonings.
Add to salad mixture.
Toss to coat.
Cover and chill.

title: happy hippo's honey hermits
directions: Place peanut butter in a cup; add honey to peanut butter.
Add powdered milk to peanut butter.
Add crispy rice cereal.
Stir well, then you roll them into balls.
Place them in a tray and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: sauerkraut and polish sausage
directions: Drain and rinse sauerkraut.
Cut Polish sausage into 1-inch pieces.
Put in pan; add 1 cup water, apple, carrot and caraway seed.
Cook until meat, carrot and apples are done and very little juice left.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef in thinnest possible slices.
Pound in flour, salt and pepper.
Cut into strips, about 3 x 1/2-inch.
Dice onions and fry slowly until soft and just turning yellow.
Then add meat and saute until well seared.
Add tomato paste and enough consomme to just cover.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Simmer until tender.
Transfer to top of double boiler and add sour cream and mushrooms.
Reheat in double boiler when ready to serve.
Serve on rice.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Drain carrots after cooking.
Add cheese and butter.
Stir well and add milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir again.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in greased dish.
Put crushed chips on top the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: cukes and cream
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin; processor or peeler can be used. Chop onions into small pieces.
Soak in refrigerator for 2 hours. Drain and squeeze out moisture.
Add pepper and serve swimming in cream.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix together. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for approx. 6 min. Let Cool.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Set oven to 300°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, toast nuts for 15 to 20 minutes.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and stir in pecans.
Melt butter in the 9 x 13-inch pan; add coated pecan mixture.
Roast 30 minutes more.
Stir every 10 minutes; cool and store in airtight container.
You may substitute walnuts.

title: pork chops with spanish rice
directions: In oven, slowly brown pork chops in heated oil.
Drain. Sprinkle pork chops with salt, chili powder and black pepper.
Add rice, onions and green peppers.
Pour in tomatoes with liquid, breaking the tomatoes into pieces with a wooden spoon.
Cover and simmer 1 hour at 350°, stirring occasionally.

title: banana punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Cool.
Add banana pulp.
Mix with all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Freeze.
Before serving, add ginger ale.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat egg and add vanilla, milk, bread and sugar.
Set aside for 30 minutes, then put into a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, raisins and butter over the top.
If you double this recipe, use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Set baking dish in pan of water in oven, if possible.
Done when silver knife comes out clean.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Make your own chicken
broth
or
use canned.
Heat the chicken broth to a boil,
then turn down to a simmer.
Add the amount of tortilla strips
you want to.
Don't simmer too long or strips will become
mushy.
Ladle
into bowls and add green onions and sprinkle with
cheese.
Sometimes I will mix everything into the soup and bring it to a boil, remove it from the heat and serve.

title: tabbouleh(middle east salad)
directions: Soak wheat in enough water to cover.
Place in fridge until liquid is almost all absorbed (about 3/4 of an hour).

title: egg and cheese souffle
directions: Butter 2-quart casserole dish.
Trim crusts and cube bread. Layer bread and cheese in casserole making two layers of each.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread/cheese, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While baking casserole, fry bacon crisp.
Crumble bacon on top of casserole the last 10 minutes of baking.
Serve immediately.

title: maine's million dollar fudge
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and boil 6 minutes.
Put the semi-sweet chocolate and the sweet chocolate, marshmallow cream and nuts into a large bowl.
Pour the boiling syrup over ingredients in the bowl; beat until chocolate is melted.
Pour into pans; let stand a few hours before cutting.
Store in tin box.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Combine onion and celery with remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.
Better if prepared a day ahead.
Freezes well.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger. Drain. Layer sliced potatoes on bottom of Pyrex dish; layer onions and another layer of potatoes. Salt and pepper. Layer hamburger next and vegetarian soup. Layer cheese. Layer mushroom soup and 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 400° about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock pot and cook on low for 12 - 14 hours.
Mix with mixer and put in jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt and set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients well, then add flour mixture.
Roll into small balls and place onto greased cookie sheet.
Press with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan pies(makes 3 pies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, syrup and butter.
Stir in pecans.
Bake near center of oven. Center may be soft, but will be firm when cool.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Mix soup, garlic and oregano in a small saucepan; heat until warm.
Spread soup mixture over buns and top with cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Be careful, it's hot!

title: american beauty cake
directions: Combine food coloring and cocoa.
Let stand.
Cream the shortening and gradually beat in sugar; add eggs and color mixture. Beat well.
Add buttermilk alternately with salt and flour mixture; beat well.
Beat in vanilla.
Remove from mixer and sprinkle baking soda over batter.
Pour vinegar over soda and stir in thoroughly. Bake in 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Cool.
Cut each layer in half (4 layers) and ice.

title: flowerpot dirt cake
directions: In a food processor or blender, crush the cookies until fine; set aside.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries.
Let start to gel and pour over cheese layer. Refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Combine tapioca, orange jello and vanilla pudding with 1/2 cup cold orange juice.
Add to hot orange juice and cook until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
(Use heavy pan as it burns easily.)
Let cool completely.
Fold in whipped topping and oranges.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: deer chili
directions: In a large pot, brown meat, onions and pepper; drain.
Add rest of ingredients except beans.
Use enough water to make it as thick as you like.
Add beans after it starts cooking.
Simmer at least one hour.
May use all deer meat.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix and roll out.
Cut and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400°.

title: raspberry cream pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie dish with dough.
Pour berries in and sprinkle with flour.
Add enough milk until almost full.
Pour sour cream around top of berries.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° until done.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat the eggs for 3 minutes. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in softened butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 pie.

title: big taco
directions: Brown the ground beef well, then drain off grease. Stir in 1 package taco seasoning with 1/4 cup water; heat. Serve in layers in this order: meat, lettuce, tomato, onion, crushed chips and cheese sauce (melted Velveeta mixed with tomatoes and green chilies).

title: skillet scallops
directions: This is a nice company dish.
Looks as though you spent hours working with it.

title: sliced dill pickles
directions: Boil first five ingredients; bring to a good boil.
Put pickles in jars.
Into each put 1 teaspoon mustard seed and a head of fresh dill.
Pour mixture over and seal.
Use medium size pickles and slice like hamburger slices.

title: creamy dijon cocktail sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Serve on hot or cold cooked fish.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: crushed pineapple whip
directions: Drain pineapple and let set on layers of paper towels for 30 minutes.
Combine Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add pineapple and jello (dry).
Mix well.
Cool and serve.

title: toffee
directions: Butter	a square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Spread pecans in pan. Heat
sugar
and
butter to boiling point, stirring constantly. Boil
over	medium	heat,
stirring constantly for 7 minutes. Immediately
spread mixture evenly over nuts in pan. Sprinkle chocolate
pieces
over hot mixture.
Place a baking sheet	over pan so contained heat will melt chocolate.	Spread melted chocolate
over
candy while hot.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares and chill until firm.
Makes about 3 dozen candies.

title: mexican bean soup(frijoles a la charra)
directions: Simmer until guests are ready.
Happy holiday!

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Saute onion in butter, blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in chicken and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in Carnation evaporated milk.
Heat to a serving temperature (do not boil).
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: lemon couscous
directions: Bring water to a boil in saucepan; stir in couscous.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork. Combine couscous with tomato, cucumber, scallions, parsley and mint; toss.
Combine lemon juice and next 4 ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour over couscous mixture and toss.
Yields 8 (1-cup) servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Add onion and pepper.
Add broth and salsa. Bring to a boil.
Add corn, then rice.
Turn off and cover for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and let melt.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter or oleo in water.
When again boiling, add flour and salt.
Stir rapidly until mixture cleans from sides of pan. Cool.
Then add 1 egg at a time, beating until smooth after each one.
After last egg, beat for 3 minutes.
Drop by tablespoon on greased baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in 450° oven, then turn oven down to 300°.
Bake 30 minutes more.
When cool, cut lid off, scoop out some inner pulp and fill with Minnesota Frosting (found in Cakes and Cookies section).
Very good and inexpensive to make.

title: persimmon pudding with sauce
directions: Mix together.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: burgers 'n sprouts
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into 8 patties.
Broil patties 3-inches from heat about 5 minutes on each side. Serves 8. Contains 190 calories.

title: beef stroganoff sandwich
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Cut bread lengthwise in half, butter.
Place on baking sheet.
Add sour cream to meat.
Spoon onto bread.
Sprinkle with tomato, pepper and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: squash lorraine
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: grandma's sour cream corn bread
directions: In bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until moistened.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bread tests done.
Yields 9 servings.
Freeze leftovers in a freezer bag.

title: red sauerkraut
directions: Fry the onion in the bacon grease and oleo until tender.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.

title: marinated salmon steaks
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Place fish in shallow baking dish. Combine orange juice, soy sauce, parsley, oil, garlic and basil. Pour over fish.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours, turning steaks occasionally.
Drain, reserve marinade.
Place fish in a well-greased wire grill basket or cook directly on grill. Grill over medium coals about 8 minutes or until fish is light brown.
Baste with marinade, then turn and grill an additional 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Reheat remaining marinade to boiling.
Transfer fish to serving platter and drizzle with marinade.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, 1 at a time and beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Add jar of chopped maraschino cherries, well drained. Add walnuts.
Fold in cherries and walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until done.
Start cake in cold oven and do not open oven door while baking.
Gas oven 325°; electric oven 300°.

title: pumpkin oat bran muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine pumpkin, milk, egg whites and oil.
Stir just enough until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Spray muffin cups with vegetable cooking spray.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: kraut wieners
directions: Heat oil, green pepper and onion.
Add remaining.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: blonde brownies
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and add 1 pound brown sugar.
Cool. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour with baking powder and salt. Add to mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 36 brownies.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar, dash of salt. Pour into pastry shell. Bake 50 minutes. Until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and butter and form into balls; refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt 12 ounces chocolate and 1/2 bar wax. Dip balls into chocolate.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Delicious.

title: lentil burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and chill.
Form into 8 patties. Grill or fry in olive oil.
Serve on hamburger rolls spread with butter or ghee.
Serves 8.

title: pecan-crusted salmon
directions: (May want to cut ingredients in half.)

title: tuna in sherry sauce
directions: Place top chafing pan direct on heat.
Melt butter in pan. Slowly stir in flour until smooth.
Add cream gradually and season with salt.
Stir slowly until mixture reaches boiling point.
Add tuna, mushrooms and pimentos.
Heat and stir slowly to the boiling point.
Add egg and wine.
Stir slightly and serve at once on buttered toast.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy brat stew
directions: In a 3 quart casserole, stir together preceding ingredients. Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: In a 4-quart mixing bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/2 cup water. Let stand 5 minutes. Add remaining water and 3 cups flour. Beat until smooth, about 100 strokes. Cover with plastic wrap for 6 to 24 hours. Add shortening and salt. By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Knead on a floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 5 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Punch dough down. Divide into 2 parts. On a lightly floured surface, roll or pat dough into a 7 x 11-inch rectangle. Place smooth side of dough down. Roll up tightly, starting from the short side. Pinch edges and ends to seal. Place in greased 8 x 4-inch bread pans. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour. Carefully brush breads with melted butter. Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on a wire rack. Yield: 2 loaves.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats, then cover it.
Let stand 20 minutes. Beat butter until creamy; add sugar and mix.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Stir in oat mixture.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture and blend.
Pour in a greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Let stand for 3 minutes and presto, you're done.

title: english toffee dessert
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add toffee.
Stir well until toffee is melted.
Cool.
Sauce thickens as it cools.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles, drain and pour into casserole dish.
Drain tuna and mix in.
Stir in mayo, milk and can of soup.
Chop onion and stir in.
Stir in Cheddar cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Put apples in 2-quart container; add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and cook on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add more water, if needed, but only enough to keep apples from sticking.
Apples are done when they mash easily with fork.
Add all ingredients and let cool.

title: turtle delight
directions: Pour pears and juice into small bowl.
Add several drops green food coloring.
Soak pears until green.
Lay each pear half on a plate, hollow side down.
Use four pecan halves on each pear to make turtle legs.
Use a grape for a head and two cloves for eyes. Remove cloves before eating the grape!

title: meatloaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots covered in small amount of water (slightly salted) for 15 minutes.
Add green pepper and cook 3 minutes more.
Drain. Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce in a separate pan.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in vegetables and pineapple; heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Melt butter and add salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Stir in egg and apples.
Pour into unbaked shell and cover with full top or cut 1 crust in strips and form a lattice top.
(Put 3 slices in full top.)
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover edges of pie crust with aluminum foil.
Remove during last 15 minutes of baking.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Combine butter and sugar.
Add raisins and nuts and stuff into cavity of apples.
Place apples in individual serving dishes.
Pour 1 tablespoon apple juice or water over each apple.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook 8 minutes or until tender.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put the cookies in blender and make crumbs. Melt the margarine and mix in crumbs. Spread 2/3 of this in loaf pan. Let set until you get second layer ready.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a glass bowl.
Lay stick of butter on top of mixture, microwave for 2 minutes.
Mix well with milk as needed, add pecans and put on a buttered dish.
Place in the fridge. for 1 hour.
Cut and serve.
Keep in a cool place.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill until solid and serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars and pudding mix in large mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: boogar hollow macaroni 'n chez
directions: Cook according to directshuns macaroni; drain.
Beat 3 aigs. Add salt 'n peppah to taste.
Add mix 'n then mix up.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add sour milk and blend in; mix together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in zucchini.
Put in well-greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: quantity punch
directions: Combine juices and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients just before serving.
Makes 75 four ounce servings.

title: beef 'n cream cheese roll
directions: Mix onion with softened cream cheese.
Lay 2 rows (5 pieces each) of beef down and overlap each other.
Spread cream cheese mixture over beef.
Roll up lengthwise.
Refrigerate before cutting into pieces.
Serve on crackers.

title: lemon strawberry punch
directions: Add strawberries to prepared lemonade.
Just before serving add ginger ale and ice cubes.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes and onions until done; sieve.
Add next 7 ingredients and boil for 10 minutes.
Pour into jars and cook 15 minutes in hot water bath.

title: zucchini or apple bread
directions: Chop nuts and shred zucchini (about 1 1/2 cups).
Mix oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon; mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts, zucchini and raisins. Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 5-inch pan.

title: skillet zucchini
directions: Saute zucchini and onions in margarine.
Cover until tender. Mix together 1/2 cup sour cream, milk, salt, paprika and poppy seed.
Add to squash.

title: hot orchard peach cup
directions: Combine juice, brown sugar, 2 cinnamon sticks and margarine in Dutch oven.
Heat to a boil.
Remove from heat; discard cinnamon sticks.
Add Schnapps, if desired.
Garnish with additional cinnamon sticks, if desired.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be made ahead, then put in oven just before serving.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of 13 X 9 cake pan; sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan. Thoroughly combine thawed strawberries and syrup with dry gelatin; set aside. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Blend at low speed until moistened. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter evenly over marshmallows and spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown and toothpick comes out clean when inserted in center. Serve warm or cool with ice cream.

title: submarines
directions: Cut lengthwise in thirds (3 pieces bread). Spread each with butter. Put 1 piece of each meat and cheese slices on the middle and bottom slice. Spread with sandwich spread. Wrap sandwich with foil. Place 3 or 4-inches from fire on grill or 350° oven until cheese melts, about 15 minutes. Enjoy.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes
and
onion slow until tender. Mash potatoes. Add broth, seasoning and half and half. Simmer. Serve.

title: mac salad
directions: Chill for several hours before serving.

title: cucumber salad scandinavian
directions: Peel cucumber, if necessary.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Chill 2 hours or longer in refrigerator before serving.

title: potato-hamburger casserole(good)
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Make layers of potatoes, onion and hamburger in 3-quart casserole.
Cover with mixed soups.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered. (I also used microwave until done.)

title: cabbage rolls
directions: First cook the rice; set aside to cool.
Set large pot of boiling water (salted) on work place; add cabbage leaves and cover and set aside.
Combine meat, chopped onion, egg, cooked rice, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Drain water from cabbage; roll meat mixture in the leaves and secure with toothpicks.
Take a large saucepot and add 2 teaspoons oil. Place rolls in pan.
Take 1 teaspoon brown sugar and add to tomato sauce.
Pour over rolls. Cover and simmer for about an hour or you can bake in the oven.

title: cold veggie pizza
directions: Note:
Use 3/4 cup (more or less, to individual taste) of the vegetables and cheeses.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, Crisco oil and vanilla; add the other ingredients. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 13 x 9 cake pan.

title: butternut squash and cider soup
directions: Heat a medium size saucepan over low heat.

Add the shallot, garlic and water. Cook until the shallot and garlic are softened, being careful not to burn, about 2 minutes. Add the squash and the chicken broth and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat, cover and simmer until the squash is soft, about 20 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Combine contents of both packets from rice Florentine package, butter and water in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, tightly covered, for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Shape sausage into thin patties.
Fry in skillet until brown and crisp; drain on paper towels.
Crumble sausage into cooked rice mixture; mix well.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in cream.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Place packages of broccoli on paper towel and microwave on High for 4 1/2 minutes.
Place chicken in casserole; cover with Saran Wrap.
Cook on High for 7 minutes.
Remove chicken and slice.
Arrange broccoli spears in casserole.
Place chicken over the broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry. Pour over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Heat 1 minute. Serve and enjoy!

title: chicken fingers
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Mix ingredients; put chicken into mixture.
Fry until brown on all sides in about 1 1/2 cups oil.
(Batter puffs up like the Chinese chicken fingers.)

title: manhattan quahog chowder
directions: Over
low
heat, cook salt pork in large saucepan until fat is extracted.
Remove salt pork (optional).

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Cream butter and 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Add egg yolks,
one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and soda. Add 1/3 flour, then 1/2 cup sour cream alternately until used. Beat egg whites; add 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into cake mix.
Pour into greased and
floured
Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, salt and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add half of flour.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour and flavoring.
Add bananas and pecans.
Pour into small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bread springs back when touched.

title: "green" salad
directions: When jello has thickened, add the other ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan or 8-inch round cake pan.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate oil cake
directions: Mix with mixer oil and buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients, except boiling water.
Mix well.
Add boiling water slowly and beat on low speed until mixed.
Will be very thin. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake as directed on box.
Immediately after cake is removed from oven, poke full of holes.
Pour cream of coconut over cake while hot.
Let cake cool.

title: crescent roll casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in mushrooms, cheese and tomato sauce.
Pour into rectangular, glass casserole.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Mix together sour cream, oregano and chili powder.
Spread small amount of mixture on each roll and roll up. Place on top of meat mixture and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until browned.

title: connie's seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; chill.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: mexican beef hash casserole(serves 8)
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and beef until meat is browned.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in dish, cover and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 60 minutes.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: three three and one ice cream
directions: In chilled ice cream freezer can, mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and cream.
Mix together oranges, bananas and lemon. Add to above mixture and add enough whole milk to bring mixture up to fill line on can and freeze per your freezer instructions. Remove paddle.
Best if packed 2 to 4 hours in salt and ice before eating.

title: easy onion rings
directions: Slice onions and separate rings.
Mix pancake mix with water to make thick paste.
Add onions, few at a time, to mixture.
Stir and deep-fry in hot cooking oil.

title: quick macaroni and cheese dish
directions: Place cooked macaroni in a bowl.
Mix with cheese soup; mix well.
Pour into a baking dish.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs on top.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients at once in a large bowl.
Beat real well. Bake in greased loaf pans at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Roll out to be filled with fruit pie filling of your choice.
Makes approximately 30 pies.
Fry pies in Puritan or Crisco oil for best pies.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Toss.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cook slowly until crisp-tender.

title: weight watchers snickers pie
directions: Soften ice cream in bowl.
Combine peanut butter, Cool Whip and pudding.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in quiche dish and freeze. Cut in eight pieces.
Each piece has 30 calories.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Stir together moist ingredients. Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients until just moistened. Add chocolate chips. Spoon batter into paper lined muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: rocky road bars
directions: In medium saucepan, melt chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows and chopped nuts.
Spread in a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until chocolate is firm.
Cut into squares.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Prepare cake by package directions.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until cake is done.
Remove and punch holes with toothpick in top of cake.

title: three layered devil's food cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: no bake "special k" cookies
directions: Bring margarine, sugar and Karo to a full rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove; stir in peanut butter.
Let cool.
Stir in the Special K and peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: chicken with sweet and sour
directions: Be sure the onion soup mix is thoroughly combined before measuring.
Place the chicken pieces, skin side down, in an 8-inch baking dish or a 10-inch Corning Ware skillet without the metal trim.
Combine salad dressing, onion mix and apricot preserves. Spoon half over the chicken pieces.
Cook in microwave for 12 minutes.
Rearrange chicken pieces in dish and turn skin side up. Spoon remaining sauce on chicken pieces.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Total cooking time: 19 minutes.
Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Break up head of lettuce in cake pan.
Layer frozen peas and water chestnuts.
Frost with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese and sugar.
Layer with sliced onion, chopped eggs and crumbled bacon.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cover and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: creamy hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add chocolate and melt it, stirring so it won't "catch".
Add sugar and milk.
Stir until sugar is completely dissolved. Add 2 tablespoons vanilla.
Place in 1-quart container.
When ready to use, place what you need in pan.
Bring to rolling boil for a minute and serve over ice cream or dessert.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Blend all ingredients, except corn, cheese, chilies and bell pepper for about 20 seconds.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown. (May have to cook more slowly than this; takes a while for middle.)

title: savory cauliflower
directions: Cut cone shaped wedge out of cauliflower core.
Place cauliflower and water into 1
quart micro-proof casserole. Cook, covered on high for 9 minutes, turning over halfway through. Drain.
Mix mayo, onion, mustard, and salt. Spoon sauce over top of cauliflower.
Lay cheese slices on top.
Cook, uncovered on 70 (roast) for 1 minute or until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute 2 minutes (do not burn).
Stir in broth and tortellini. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, mix in 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer approximately 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, spinach and basil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: baked bean medley
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
(Drain lima beans and kidney beans first.)
Mix and bake at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes.
Be prepared to have your family request this dish for all get togethers.

title: spinach-phyllo triangles
directions: Drain thawed spinach well, pressing between paper towels until barely moist.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet until tender.
Add spinach, Parmesan cheese and next 7 ingredients.
Cut sheets of phyllo lengthwise into 3-inch strips. Working with 1 strip at a time, brush each strip lightly with melted butter.
Keep remaining strips covered.
Place 2 teaspoons spinach mixture at base of phyllo strips.
Fold the right bottom corner over to form a triangle.
Continue folding back and forth into a triangle to end of strip.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: frosty strawberry dessert
directions: *Reserve 1/3 cup for topping.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar with cornmeal, flour, butter, nutmeg, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs and milk.
Set aside for 1 hour.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: orange jello whip
directions: Bring pudding and water to a boil, until thickened.
Add in jello and fruit.
Chill (best overnight).
Stir in Cool Whip or Dream Whip (already whipped according to package directions). Chill and serve.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine flour, baking powder, 1 cup of the sugar and milk in a bowl; mix well. Pour into baking dish.
Arrange apple slices on top of mixture. Sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and remaining 1/2 cup of sugar. Pour 1/2 cup of water over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed; add lemon pudding from box, eggs and oil; mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: old fashioned pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Soften yeast in water.
Add salt and sugar.
Mix in flour and knead into a smooth dough.
Work fast. Do not allow mixture to rise.
Dust rolling pin and surface lightly with flour.
Roll dough to desired thickness and cut into strips.
Roll strips between palms of hands until desired length. Lay on greased baking sheet and shape into pretzel.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with salt or sesame seed.
Bake until golden, 15 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10.
Great with cheese sauce or sweet mustard.

title: french vanilla fruit delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
