Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Prepare, bake and cool cake, following package directions for no-cholesterol recipe.

title: pecan honey cookies
directions: Mix sugar and honey; add eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients, stir until smooth.
Make into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheets.
Place pecan halves on flattened balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute the ground chuck and onions.
Add to the squash.
Add cheese and mushrooms if desired.
Season to taste and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wonderful waffles
directions: In a medium bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In another medium bowl, mix egg yolks, milk and oil; stir into flour mixture.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites with electric mixer on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Prepare waffle iron according to manufacturer's directions.
Using 1/2 cup batter for each waffle, bake on preheated waffle iron until steaming stops and waffle is golden brown.
Makes 9 waffles.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, combine beef shank, water, salt, marjoram, oregano, bay leaves and peppercorns.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 3 hours.
Remove shank and strain broth.
Cool broth and skim off fat.
Cut meat into small pieces and return to broth.
Add vegetables.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Adjust seasonings.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown meat over medium heat.
Drain.
Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire.
Pour into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove dish from oven; stir.
Arrange biscuits around edge of dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake until biscuits are a golden brown.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Radishes, pepper, etc., may be added.

title: nut bread dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Cover with plastic and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: hazel fishers' date - chocolate cake
directions: Place dates, boiling water and soda in bowl and let stand. Cream together sugar and Crisco or margarine.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Alternate flour mix and liquid poured from dates, then add half of chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured pan and cover with chopped nuts and remaining half of chocolate chips.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 325°. Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch (deep) pan.

title: hearty chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; season meat with garlic and cumin.
Drain.
Add all ingredients, except kidney beans.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: artichoke and four cheese pie
directions: *I use Tarrytown Bakery "Birrittella's pizza dough" which can be found in the dairy case of any major food chain found in Westchester.
The dough should stand about 8 hours to room temperature before using.
Makes a great pie crust for any quiche.

title: apple stuffed pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cut a slit in the pork chops from outer edge to bone. Fill pockets loosely and secure with toothpicks.
Season chops to taste. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in 4 or 5 cups water until tender.
Mix broth and soup together.
Bring to a boil.
Put a layer of dressing, 1/2 of soup, all of chicken and then use remaining dressing and soup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit jam
directions: Mix fruit, pineapple juice and honey and boil 2 minutes.
Add gelatin which has been softened in the cold water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Fill containers and freeze.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Add cheese and mushroom soup.
Mix all ingredients; put into casserole.
Top with more cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 360° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken, broccoli and rice
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, combine soup, rice and water or milk.
Add about half the onion rings, slightly crumbled.
Arrange chicken on top of rice mixture and season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Top with rest of onion rings and return to oven for 10 minutes longer.
Can use skim milk.
Red pepper may perk up sauce.
I baked chicken and rice for 1 hour and when I added the onion rings on top and put back in oven for 10 minutes, I left uncovered.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir together dry ingredients and add to other mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove and place 1 Kiss on each, pressing until edges crack.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes more.
Store airtight.

title: barbecued corned beef sandwiches
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in skillet.
Bring mixture just to boiling point.
Add corned beef; reduce heat to low.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently, until most of liquid is absorbed. Spoon corned beef mixture on bottom half of buns.
Cover with bun tops.

title: pickle cucumber or zucchini
directions: Mix and bring first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Add cucumbers or zucchini.
Let boil 5 minutes.
Put onion in sterilized jar and seal.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on white bread circles.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Place flour and salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add 3 tablespoons water.
Stir and add enough remaining water so dough barely holds together and forms a ball.
Place dough on floured board.
Roll into 2 rectangles, approximately 24 x 15-inches.
Cut dough into 6 (7-inch) squares.

title: pecan shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla. Sift flour and salt. Add flour (a little at a time) to butter and sugar mixture; mix well. Add pecans and almond extract. Chill dough at least 1 hour. (It helps to divide the dough, make 2 flat pieces and place in large, plastic storage bags.) Roll out dough and cut out cookies. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crawfish bordelaise
directions: Cook onion in
butter,	and
the wine, the meat and the cream sauce with	seasoning.
Boil
up
once and serve hot (on toast if desired) or in patty shells.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and stir.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High. Add margarine and vanilla; stir well and microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Add baking soda.
Mix well and spread thinly onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and break apart into bite-size pieces.
(You can mix entire recipe in a 4-cup Pyrex bowl.)

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender; drain and arrange in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place tomatoes along outside edge.
Dot with butter.
Blend soup and lemon juice in a bowl until smooth.
Pour along center of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: candied sweet pickles
directions: Heat this mixture to boil and pour over slices.
You may need more of the mixture depending on how many pickles you have.
Pour this mixture off and reheat to boiling 4 days and pour back over.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spray 9-inch pan with Pam.
Lay apples in pan; pour water over them.
Spoon sugar and cinnamon over apples.
With pastry blender, mix margarine and dry ingredients until fine crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool sliced like apple pie.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Mix other ingredients in blender; add to potatoes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cover with topping.
Cover with foil or lid and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: every day broccoli cheese chicken
directions: In skillet brown chicken in hot margarine about 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off any fat.

title: britainy stew or shepherd's pie
directions: Place lamb in casserole dish.
Place sliced potatoes on top. Cover with lamb gravy.
Top with green beans.
Add fresh onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fantastic butter crust
directions: Combine butter with sugar.
Add flour.
Mix just until a dough will form.
Press evenly over bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan. Bake in 375°
oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In a 3-quart metal mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together the gelatin, brown sugar, salt and pumpkin pie spice.
Stir in milk. With a whisk, beat in the egg yolks, then the pumpkin.
Place the bowl over a saucepan of boiling water; cook, stirring often until heated through and gelatin and sugar have dissolved, about 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: bishops bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add chips and nuts.
Beat eggs into large bowl.
Add sugar.
Dump flour mixture into eggs; mix.
Pat into pan (loaf).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: shrimp scampi with rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter; add garlic and parsley and saute lightly.
Blend in cooking wine and salt and pepper.
Add shrimp and saute quickly until they are tender, approximately 5 minutes.
Arrange shrimp on a bed of rice pilaf and serve the sauce of the shrimp.

title: grouper saute
directions: Simmer onions and peppers, if you like, in skillet with small amount of butter and enough water to keep moist.
When onions are half cooked, add pieces of fish, precut into strips or squares. Fish will break into smaller pieces as it cooks, but real large pieces of fish don't work well.
Season with garlic powder and hot spice seasoning. (I used garlic salt and Seafood Magic.) Keep moist by adding water.
Cook over medium-low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Let water boil.
Add corn meal and salt.
Set boiler in pan of hot water on burner.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy; beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Blend in melted butter; stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea - reston chorale
directions: Mix in bowl or shake in large jar.
Store in airtight container.

title: veggie pizza appetizers
directions: Spray a 15 inch jelly roll pan with non-stick cooking spray, pull out the dough sealing the edges.
Bake according to pkg directions, leave in the pan to cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place chicken in pot with water, salt, parsley, onion and celery and boil until cooked.
Remove chicken from pot.
Remove skin and cut up into 1-inch pieces.
Drain the chicken stock and reserve.
Now melt the butter/margarine and add flour, stirring constantly.
Gradually add 8 cups chicken stock, keep stirring until it begins to thicken.
In the meantime, beat the three egg yolks, add about 1/2 cup of the sauce to the egg yolks.
Mix and slowly pour the yolks back into the thickened sauce.
If the sauce is too bland, add a chicken bouillon or two for taste. Additionally, add the Tabasco sauce (a few shakes) and 1/4 cup sherry (optional).

title: gene's meatballs
directions: Mix jelly, chili sauce and, if desired, chopped onion and pepper.
Put in crock-pot.
Mix bread crumbs into ground beef and form meatballs.
Put meatballs into sauce in crock-pot and cook on high until meatballs are brown.

title: apple pie
directions: In pie pan, put pie crust.
Slice apples and put in pie crust. Mix up cinnamon, flour, nutmeg and butter (it will be sort of crumbly).
Put all over top of apples, then take sour cream and spread all over top of apples and mixture.
Put crust on top and spread margarine all over top.
Punch holes all in top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy beef burgundy
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake for 3 hours at 350°.

title: spiced orange iced tea
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine 3 cups cold water, cinnamon sticks, nutmeg and cloves, bring to a boil and remove from heat. Add tea bags and brew 5 minutes. Remove tea bags and strain mixture.
Pour tea into serving picture and add remaining water, orange juice and sugar, mixing well. Chill, serve over ice, garnish with orange slices.

title: pet-ritz easy caramel apple pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine caramel pieces and flour. Add apples, caramel topping and lemon juice; mix well. Pour mixture into crust. Top with pecans. Bake on preheated baking sheet at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until crust has browned. Cool.

title: crunch cake
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar, gradually.
Continue to cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add all of flour at one time and mix well.
Bake in paper-lined tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: raviola
directions: Heat butter.
Cook green pepper and onion; add meat.
Turn several times until all ingredients are coated with butter.
In a stew pan, cook tomatoes, salt, sugar, soda and chili powder until reduced in bulk to about half.
Cook with meat mixture about 20 minutes.

title: everybody's favorite beef stew(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Combine flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Coat meat cubes in seasoned flour.
Brown in oil in Dutch oven; add soup, 2 1/2 cups water, onion and basil.
Cover and bake at 375° about 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots and wine.
Cover and bake 1 hour longer.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Form into balls.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls and put on waxed paper until firm.

title: cousin pam's icebox dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, nuts and margarine in oblong pan and brown in oven at 350°.
Cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, mix the sugar and evaporated milk together.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cook until soft boil stage. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until blended. Don't beat, just stir until blended.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve the juice in a small saucepan.
Set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cup, bring to a boil.
Place gelatin in a bowl; add boiling liquid and stir until dissolved.
Cool until thickened slightly.
Beat up whipping cream, then gradually add sugar.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese.
Blend well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Chill 3 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute onion; add beef and brown.
Add sauce.
Combine beef mixture and cooked macaroni.
In a large casserole dish, layer macaroni mixture, then cheese, then pepperoni.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: mashed potato bake
directions: Mash potatoes and season as for mashed potatoes.
Mix cream cheese and onion dip with potatoes.
Add milk if needed to make them nice and fluffy.
Put in casserole; sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
You can make this ahead of time and freeze for at least a month.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Melt the chocolate chips and wax in a pan over water.
Roll first mixture into balls.
Dip in melted chocolate with toothpick.
Makes about 60 balls.

title: faux carrot cake muffins with cream cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a six count muffin pan heavily with vegetable oil spray.
Mix together 1 Tbsp. each of baking mix and wheat bran and sprinkle over the sprayed muffin pan, coating each cup well.
This will prevent sticking.
Mix the remaining ingredients by hand with a wire whisk until blended. Divide the mixture evenly into the six muffin cups.
Bake for approximately 20-25 minutes.
To test if done: They should be browned and done when a wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: "sara" misu(prep time: 20 minutes)
directions: In medium bowl, beat together cheese, sugar and vanilla. Fold in chopped chocolate. Set aside several berries for garnish. If using strawberries, thinly slice remaining berries. Cut cake horizontally into 3 slices. Place bottom slice on a serving platter. Drizzle with half of the coffee. Spread with one-fourth (or about 1/3 cup) of the cheese mixture and top with half of the berries. Spread bottom of center cake slice with another one-fourth (or about 1/3 cup) of the cheese mixture and place, cheese side down, on top of berries. Drizzle with remaining coffee. Repeat layers of cheese mixture and berries. Spread bottom of top cake slice with remaining cheese mixture and place cheese side down on top of berries.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400° to 450°. Put oil in iron skillet (small) and put in the oven to heat. Mix milk, egg, mayo and meal in bowl. Pour hot grease from skillet into mixture and stir. Pour into skillet and return to oven. Bake until brown.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 of flour, the sugars, egg, vanilla, baking powder and soda.
Beat until mixed good.
Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in cereal, coconut and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute.
Remove and cool on rack.
Makes about 54.

title: coconut pie
directions: Separate eggs (use egg whites for meringue).
Place all other ingredients in a double boiler and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue and brown.

title: company come chicken
directions: Roll a slice of cheese inside of chicken breast.
Wrap with 2 strips of bacon.
Secure with toothpicks.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over the chicken.
Bake uncovered in a casserole at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: southern bean relish
directions: Drain and empty beans into a bowl.
Add the peppers, onions, sugar and mayonnaise; toss lightly.
Chill.
May be served on lettuce with fried chicken.

title: reubens
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in shallow pan.
Serve with rye bread and Thousand Island dressing.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over remainder of ingredients.

title: egg salad
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water; place bowl over boiling water and stir until gelatine is dissolved.
Cool and beat into mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients.

title: cheese balls
directions: Roll in chopped pecans.
Makes 1 or 2 cheese balls.

title: easy dessert
directions: Mix all together and serve as dessert.
Substitute mandarin oranges and orange jello, if desired.
Delicious and easy.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine cornbread mix and salt in a 2-quart saucepan. Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until very thick, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Blend 1/2 cup cooked mixture into egg yolks.
Blend in remaining cooked mixture until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased round 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve immediately.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 tube pans (makes 2 cakes).
Soak poppy seed and extract in buttermilk overnight.
Cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg yolks.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Blend well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into pans.
Add sugar/cinnamon mix to each pan. Add rest of batter on top to each pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole in 275° oven for 5 hours or cook in crock-pot for 5 hours or low.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add oats and water.
Mix until crumbly.

title: fresh strawberry and spinach salad(yields 12 servings)
directions: Whisk lemon juice and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add egg yolks and whisk well.
Then add oil, 2 tablespoons at a time, whisking well after each addition.
Pour over tossed spinach and strawberries.
Serve.

title: old fashion real country sling shot gravy
directions: Put grease in frying pan.
Add flour and milk.
Mix slowly (you must mix every minute).
After mixing, add a tad of water. How many does it serve?
It depends on how much you use.
After all other ingredients, add meat.

title: soft taco shells
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Heat lightly greased 6-inch skillet.
Pour slightly less than 1/4 cup batter into skillet for each shell.
Lift and tilt skillet to spread batter.
Brown on one side, flip and brown other side.
Keep warm until served.
Serve with your favorite taco ingredients and sauce.
Makes 10 to 12 shells.

title: dill pickle meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef and pork, onion, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper, pickle juice and 1/2 cup of the dill pickles.
Shape into loaf and place in roasting pan.

title: crispy macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup, milk, mustard and pepper until smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with French fried onion rings and remaining 1/2 cup of cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: shereens' imli chutni(tamarind chutney; makes 1 cup)
directions: Place tamarind in small bowl and pour the boiling water over it.
Stir and mash to separate and dissolve in water.
Discard the seeds and fiber.
Make to puree.

title: grandmother cole's coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, both milks, coconut and butter. Pour in raw pie crusts and bake at 275° until done in center. Makes 4 to 8 pies according to size.

title: tuna-cheese casserole
directions: Slice onion.
Separate into rings and saute.
Spread one side of bread with butter.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, Worcestershire sauce and salt; blend.
Place 4 slices bread in single layer in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Trim if necessary.
Top with layers of 1/2 onion rings, melted butter, tuna and cheese.
Repeat to make 2 more layers.
Pour egg mix over top with Parmesan and paprika.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Place pork chops in baking pan.
Salt and pepper lightly. Then sprinkle with brown sugar.
Mix tomato soup and catsup together and pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: carrot cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Combine and sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Break eggs in small bowl; add oil and vanilla and beat together.
Then add to sifted ingredients together with pineapple, grated carrots and pecans.
This makes a stiff mixture and it is best to fold the flour, etc., by hand.
Pour batter into greased tube pan and bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Crumble sausage in medium-sized heavy skillet and cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well. Spread bread cubes in a buttered 12 x8 x 2-inch baking dish and top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings. Beat well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tutti-frutti salad
directions: Combine all undrained fruits with the coconut and lemon juice. Sprinkle dry pudding over and toss lightly; chill overnight.
Add bananas before serving if desired.

title: buttered party nuts(microwave oven)
directions: Place butter in 3-quart casserole. Microwave (High) 45 to 60 seconds or until melted.
Mix in remaining ingredients except nuts.
Add nuts, stirring to coat.
Microwave (High) 7 to 9 minutes, or until butter is absorbed, stirring 2 to 3 times during cooking.
Spread on paper towel-lined baking sheet to dry.
Store nuts in tightly covered container.
Makes 4 cups.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and up sides of 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef in large chunks; drain.
Place beef, broccoli and tomato in potato shells.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix water, jello, strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Put 1/3 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Spread sour cream over chilled mixture.
Slice bananas over sour cream in a single layer.
Pour remaining jello mixture over top.
Chill until firm.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus in bottom of Pyrex dish (greased).
Layer with peas.
Repeat if needed.
Add soup and pour over asparagus. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Slice all into a crock-pot. Add water to cover and favorite seasonings to taste.
When chopping potatoes, slice across for oval shape when done.
Cover.
Let cook for about 3 hours on high.

title: raised waffles or pancakes
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Beat in rest of ingredients with rotary beater.
Cover and let rise in warm place (85°) about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir down, cover and set in refrigerator overnight.
Stir down again when ready to use.
Pour onto hot waffle iron.
Bake until brown and crisp, 3 to 4 minutes.
Makes about 8 (7-inch) waffles.

title: quick apple pie
directions: Put apples in glass oblong baking dish.
Mix margarine, sugar and egg together.
Set aside.
Lay trimmed loaf bread over top of apples.
Take the mixture you set aside and spread over top of bread.
Bake in oven at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes. Serves 8. Best when served hot with ice cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze out excess water and flake and mix into sour cream mixture.
Serve with chips and crackers.

title: company strata
directions: From 12 slices of bread, cut 12 doughnuts and holes with doughnut cutter.
Fit scraps of bread in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer the cheese, then broccoli, then ham on top of the bread.
Arrange doughnuts and holes on top.
Combine the eggs, onions, salt and dry mustard; pour over bread.
Try to moisten each doughnut and hole.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 12.
Can substitute chicken for ham.

title: apple-pineapple scallop
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 3/4 cup liquid.
Combine dry ingredients in heavy saucepan; add pineapple juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice.
Layer fruit, crumbs and cheese in buttered 2-quart casserole (pour on sauce before adding last layer of crumbs and cheese).
Cover and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour, or until apple slices are tender.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to become room temperature; blend in mayonnaise until creamy.
Stir in pineapple and hold back some of the
juice;
add
to
desired
consistency.
Stir in nuts. Serve with party crackers.

title: grrreat punch
directions: Add ingredients to bowl.
If desired, pineapple sherbet may be added for creamy punch.

title: tuna mold
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in large mold.
Let chill overnight. Unmold and garnish with parsley and pecan pieces.
Serve with assorted crackers.
This makes a large mold and is good for serving a large crowd.

title: beef roast
directions: Baste roast with A.1. steak sauce. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, oregano and flour.
Brown in hot oil and add beer, soup and onion mix.
Add mushrooms. Cook until tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Also can bake at 350° the same amount of time.
Can also be cooked in crock-pot.

title: pork chop spanish rice
directions: In large Dutch oven, slowly brown the chops in heated oil. Drain off excess oil.
Sprinkle chops with salt, chili powder and black pepper.
Add the rice, onions and chopped green peppers. Pour in the tomatoes with liquid, breaking the tomatoes into pieces with a wooden spoon.
Cover and bring to boiling over high heat. Reduce heat and simmer 35 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the pepper rings and cook 2 minutes longer or until the rice and meat are tender.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Transfer to serving platter, arranging the chops and pepper rings over the top. Makes enough for 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine veggies, cheese and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add mixture to veggies.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: chicken breasts in asparagus-wine sauce
directions: Prepare Chicken:
Coat and rub both sides of each breast with garlic and lemon pepper.
(Use more or less, depending on size.) Let stand 15 to 20 minutes, covered.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, ending with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together all but last ingredient and spoon into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add all other ingredients except Cool Whip. Mix.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour in container that comes with the ice cream freezer.
Add enough milk to fill container.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add sweet potatoes and milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a heavily floured surface; knead lightly, 8 to 10 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch round cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Thinly layer all ingredients in order given, preferably in an oblong Tupperware dish.
After making, let chill in refrigerator for about 30 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and chops or buy chopped.
Heat oil and toss in broccoli and onion.
Cook until tender (5 to 10 minutes).
Add 1 can mushroom soup and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and stir in cheese, salt and cooked rice.
Milk may be added if too thick.
Put in baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fried matzo
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients, except butter.
Melt butter in skillet.
Pour egg mixture in skillet and fry.
Stir.
When eggy, take out.

title: sausage crisp
directions: Mix the dry Bisquick, cheese and then sausage.
Roll into balls 1-inch in diameter and then mash in center with finger. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 36.

title: salmon loaf and white sauce
directions: Mince salmon and add 4 tablespoons melted butter, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and 3 beaten eggs.
Make into a loaf; set loaf pan into a pan of water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: spinach ham quiche
directions: Mix in large bowl, eggs, spinach, ham, and mushrooms.
Pour into pie shells.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 300 degrees for 50 minutes.
Can be frozen after baking.
Serve with salad!

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible, or at least 2 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown onions and celery in margarine.
Add cooked beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: lily's tea cakes
directions: Mix all
ingredients well.
Roll very thin and cut with cookie cutter and bake in a 350° oven
for
to 15 minutes. Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onions and peppers.
Combine other ingredients.
Place in a Pam-sprayed casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with cornflake crumbs.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour buttermilk over bran flakes. Let soak for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, eggs, oil and rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into paper baking cups or well-greased muffin tins.
(If I have some applesauce, I add 1/2 cup, or orange marmalade.)
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 30 large muffins.

title: bumbler celebration chicken
directions: Combine onion soup and other ingredients and pour over chicken. Place a large sheet of foil into shallow 10 x 12-inch pan.
Foil should be overlapping to cover all of chicken to make a complete seal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash. Mix eggs, butter and seasonings. Add other ingredients. Top with cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash biscuits
directions: Scald milk, butter, salt and sugar; put in squash.
Put yeast in warm water and dissolve.
Add milk mixture when cool.
Add flour.
Knead and make into biscuits.
Let rise to double size. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Fry bacon slowly.
Lay on paper towel to absorb grease.
Brown onion in bacon grease.
Add flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat; stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Cut the bacon into small pieces and add to mixture.
Also stir in potatoes. Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand until ready to serve.

title: grandma rose's pound cake
directions: Whip eggs. Mix in sugar and butter. Add whipping cream. Blend in sifted flour. Pour into greased cake pan(s). Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cheese pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Fry on both sides until golden brown.
Serve with syrup on hot cakes.

title: beef tips over rice
directions: Cut beef into cubes and place in casserole.
Combine soups and water.
Pour over beef, stirring to blend.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: jiffy cherry dessert
directions: Pour pie filling into greased 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of cherries.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When melted completely, add noodles, mixing well. Drop mixture by spoonful onto wax paper.
Cool and eat.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add 3rd mixture slowly to 2nd mixture.
After 20 minutes, add the 1st mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook pork and chicken in enough water to simmer.
Simmer covered until simmered.
Skin meat from bones.
Strain broth and skim off fat.
Save for use.
Heat chicken fat or margarine in large heavy skillet.
Add onion and cook gently until tender.

title: grandpa oakes peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo until it threads from spoon.
Add peanuts and cook until they stop popping.
Quickly stir in premeasured salt, soda and butter.
Pour out on greased pan or baking sheet.
Good stuff!

title: chicken breast bake
directions: Mix melted margarine with stuffing mix.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking
dish with half of stuffing mixture.	Add cut
up chicken
and
remaining
stuffing
mixture.
Mix
sour cream, bouillon and soup;	mix
well.
Pour over top of stuffing.	Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cocoa-cola cake
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Melt together oil, cocoa, butter and water.
Add to flour mixture.
Then add vanilla, cola and eggs. Bake in sheet cake pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water in a large container.
Add pineapple juice.
Mix well. Can be chilled or frozen for a slushier punch.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except carrots and pineapple.
Mix well.
Add carrots and pineapple, including the juice.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: steak and kidney pie
directions: Trim fat from steak and cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Remove skin and fat from kidneys and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Dredge meat with 3 tablespoons flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in a stew pan or Dutch oven.
Add onion and brown lightly.
Remove onion, brown steak cubes a few at a time in the remaining drippings.
Add onion, 1 cup beef stock (hot) and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover tightly and simmer gently for 1 to 2 hours or until tender.
Mix remaining flour with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Add to gravy to thicken.
Pour mixture into a 10-inch pie dish, invert custard cup in the center to support the crust. Roll out pastry and cover pie.
Cut small slits for steam to escape; crimp edges of pastry.
Brush with milk.
Bake in hot 425° oven for 30 minutes or until crust is golden.
Serves 6.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon, onion, mustard and garlic.
Add juice from beans, brown sugar and vinegar.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beans and ground beef, if desired.
Bake in large casserole dish for 40 minutes at 350° or simmer all day in crock-pot.

title: ground beef delight
directions: Brown beef; pour off fat.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Combine onions, cream cheese and sour cream.
In a greased casserole, layer noodles, then meat sauce, then sour cream.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: very quick potato soup
directions: Microwaved or leftover baked potatoes work just great. Combine all the ingredients in blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Reheat as required.
Great with cheese stirred in and bacon crumbled on top, too!
Perfect for busy, cold days when you need a quick perk-up.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients together in a medium mixing bowl. Make ahead 24 hours.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini, onions and green peppers coarsely and add 1/2 cup salt.
Place in large bowl, cover and let stand overnight. Next day, drain and rinse in cold water.
Then add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil for 20 to 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Will keep unsealed in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Melt butter in shallow baking dish. Stir in remaining ingredients. Roll chicken pieces in butter mixture to coat, then arrange meaty side up in single layer.
Do not cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and a rich golden color. Serves 4.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, bread, milk, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce in large mixing bowl; mix well.
Shape mixture into a loaf. Place on lightly greased rack in a broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over loaf.
Bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes, or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°. Mix the bananas, egg, salt, baking soda, sugar, baking powder and margarine. Gradually add the flour, stirring lightly. Pour the mixture into muffin tins and bake for 15 to 20 minutes until they are golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese at room temperature.
Add 1/2 cup pecans and all seasonings.
Spread the other half of pecans and parsley on waxed paper.
Place cheese in center of waxed paper and roll until covered with mixture.
(This will freeze.)

title: green rice
directions: Cook the rice.
To cook rice:
2 cups raw rice, 5 1/3 cups cold water, 1 1/3 teaspoons salt and 1 tablespoon butter.
Place all in a large saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat, then turn to low heat and cook, covered, for 25 minutes. Turn off heat and let stand covered 10 minutes.
Serves 10 and makes large ring mold.
Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Combine rice and parsley in bowl.
Add milk, salt, Worcestershire, cheese and egg, then the onion and garlic.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: orange date bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add orange rind.
Add orange juice alternately with dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Add dates and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, well-greased
on the bottom. Bake in a 350°
oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: melomakarona(greek cookies)
directions: Beat butter, oil and sugar for 15 to 20 minutes in a big bowl, add wine and other ingredients.
Mix
well
with hand.
A little at a time, add flour
until
you
make soft dough.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Use cookie cutter for shape.
Bake at 350°.

title: turkey piccata
directions: Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Moisten turkey slices; coat with mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons in skillet; saute slices until they turn a light brown.
Set meat aside in a warm place and, if desired, sprinkle lemon juice on meat.
Mix bouillon, wine and egg yolk together; add to drippings in skillet.
Stir vigorously until sauce thickens slightly.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine juices and chill.
Add cold soft drink just before serving.
Serve over ice.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set fruit aside. In a saucepan or microwave, bring pineapple juice and water to a boil. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Stir in pie filling and cola. Pour into a serving bowl. Refrigerate until slightly thickened. Fold in reserved pineapple. Refrigerate until firm. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: quick tuna-macaroni salad
directions: In bowl, combine first 8 ingredients, salt and dash of pepper. Cover and chill.
With stem end down, cut each tomato into wedges, cutting to, but not through, the base of the tomato.
Spread wedges apart slightly; sprinkle lightly with salt.
Cover and chill.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Drain 2 coconuts.
Peel and grind coconut.
Cream sugar, margarine and oil.
Beat yolks and add to mixture.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add to first mixture alternately with coconut milk. Stir in flavorings.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour in 3 well-greased 8-inch pans.
Bake at 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost and cover with fresh coconut (use 7 Minute Frosting).

title: claudia's chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream and cheese. Fry tortillas until just soft. Spoon chicken mixture on tortilla and roll up.

Place in baking dish. Saute onion, garlic and pepper. Add tomatoes and jalapeno peppers. Pour mixture over enchiladas; add grated cheese on top. Bake in oven until bubbly at 350°. (Use own judgement on peppers as everyone's taste is different.)

title: cold catsup
directions: Blend tomatoes and the cabbage; drain.
Cover with 1 cup plain salt (not iodized).
Let stand overnight, then drain well.

title: cole slaw for freezer
directions: Shred cabbage and mix with salt.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add carrot and green pepper.

title: lo-salt, lo-fat barbecue sauce(for any fish, fowl or meat, with skin and fat off)
directions: Blend well.
Simmer 25 minutes.
This bubbles and splashes. Use deep pan.
May be refrigerated up to 11 to 12 days.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: Cut carrots into thick circles.
Boil carrots in a saucepan half-filled with water until they are tender.
Remove from heat. Pour 1 1/2 cups of the hot water from the cooked carrots into a small bowl.
Add lemon juice (or rum) into the hot water.
Add cornstarch and brown sugar.
Stir until they are thoroughly dissolved.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Stir again.
Add butter and let it melt.
Add nuts and mix one last time.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt in small mixing bowl.
Stir until shortening and sugar are dissolved. Cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Meanwhile, in large bowl, let yeast stand in lukewarm water for 5 minutes, then stir and pour first mixture into large bowl.
Add 4 cups flour.
Beat well with electric mixer, then add 2 1/2 cups flour and mix by hand.
Cover and place in refrigerator at least 4 hours.
Dough will rise slightly and will keep a week to 10 days, to be used as needed.

title: simply easy pound cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Mix cream cheese, butter and eggs with an electric mixer.
Add sugar, flour and vanilla.
Blend until creamy.
Coat Bundt pan with nonstick spray and pour in batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tested done in the center.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix in order and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in greased baking dish.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: kraut and beer fudge cake
directions: Cream together margarine with sugar.
Beat eggs mixture and vanilla with margarine and sugar. Stir together dry ingredients alternately with beer to egg mixture.
Stir in kraut and nuts. Turn into two greased and floured 8-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, depending on oven and tester comes clean.
Cool.
Fill in between the cake and on the sides with your favorite vanilla frosting.
Spread a thin layer of cherry pie filling on top.
Serves 12.

title: dumplings
directions: Take a large pot of chicken broth and bring it to a rolling boil.
Add salt to taste.
Take a plate and place flour in it. Take tortillas and pick off brown spots if any.
Place tortillas in flour on both sides and tear them into small pieces.
Drop into boiling broth.
Put small amount at a time, let them boil, and then add more until you get the amount you want.
Stir easy and keep boiling for about 20 minutes.
Then add chicken, bring back to a boil and then turn the burner off.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Mix; let rise 1/2 hour.
Knead and roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter.
Fold over and brush top with butter and let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400° until done.
Also will make 2 small loaves.
Bake 30 minutes for loaves.

title: "pinch me" cake
directions: Mix yeast and water; set aside.
Mix sugars, oil, salt, milk and egg; let cool.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Add 2 cups flour; beat well.
Gradually add remaining flour; mix.
Cover; allow to rise until double.
(Let rise in a warm place at 75° to 80° for about 1 1/2 hours.)
Punch down; make into balls the size of walnuts. (Flour hands to handle dough.)
Dip balls into a mixture of sugar, cinnamon and nuts after having dipped them into melted margarine. Drop balls into solid bottom tube pan.
Allow to rise until double, about 2 hours, in a warm place or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes.
Turn out carefully.

title: meat loaf
directions: This makes one large meat loaf.
Mix all the ingredients well. Be sure to finely chop all vegetables. Garnish top with ketchup, chopped bacon or chopped ham.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: ben's favorite white apple brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients. Stir in apples and nuts. Bake in a greased 8 x 12 pan for 30 to 35 minutes. Do not bake. Cut into bars. When cool, roll in or sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yummy!

title: chicken livers in sour cream
directions: In large skillet, saut onions in butter until tender. Add chicken livers and pepper; saut 8 to 10 minutes. Add chicken bouillon cube and water; dissolve.
Stir in sour cream. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: honey chicken(a honey of a recipe!  your friends will think you slaved!)
directions: Melt butter in flat, low casserole, then add rest of the ingredients.
Mix.
Roll chicken pieces in this mixture (using only the one dish).
Arrange pieces in a single layer. Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put first 2 ingredients in bowl.
Add pudding.
Let thicken. Add bananas and lemon juice.
Serve.

title: gooey pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients together with a wooden spoon and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool about 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour icing on cake while it is still hot.

title: p.v.c.c.  play dough(not edible)
directions: Mix well with spoon or hands.
Add vegetable dye or food coloring of your choice.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir.
Place in oven casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange no bake cookies
directions: Melt
margarine.
Blend
vanilla wafers, powdered sugar and orange
juice
with hands.	You can add nuts, if you wish. Shape dough
into
teaspoon size balls and roll in coconut (or powdered sugar) as desired.	Yields 4 dozen.

title: ramen salad
directions: Break cabbage into bite sizes.
Add Ramen noodles (do not cook); break into small sizes.
Saute all nuts in butter.
Add to salad along with onions.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter over low heat; add flour and milk.
Cook until bubbly and thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix all other ingredients.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spoon potato mixture in and pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, cheese and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water in saucepan and cook over low heat until thick. Add nuts and cool. Cream shortening, add sugar and well beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Add the remaining ingredients sifted together.
Chill.

title: tangy vegetable salad
directions: If using frozen vegetables, cook until barely tender; drain and cool.
If using canned vegetables, drain well.
Combine the cold salad ingredients in large bowl.
Pour cold dressing over all and stir gently until vegetables are well-coated.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: tropical sweet potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and mash potatoes.
Add ingredients except marshmallows to potatoes.
Put in a baking dish (6 x 8-inch). Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Add marshmallows the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: fresh tomato relish
directions: Combine tomatoes, lemon juice, salt, onion and sugar.
Mix well, then stir in chives and pepper.
Chill several hours, then serve with meat, fish or poultry.
You may use freeze-dried chives in place of fresh.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cheddar-apple bread
directions: Mix all dry items together.
Add milk, margarine and eggs; mix again.
Add apples and pecans.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for approximately 70 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Toss sugar, flour and cornmeal with a fork.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except pie shell.
Beat at low speed with mixer for about 30 seconds.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes more.

title: dressing
directions: Bake in a greased casserole dish for 1/2 hour at 375° until crust browns on top.

title: white chili
directions: Add first 5 ingredients to a large pot and cook until chicken is tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except for cheese, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour. Serve topped with cheese.
If desired, hot sauce may be added.

title: microwave stuffed potato shells
directions: Scrub potatoes; pierce with fork.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 1/2 minutes or until soft to the touch, rearranging and turning over after half the time.
Let stand 5 minutes to complete cooking.
Microwave bacon on High for 30 to 60 seconds until crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Slice each potato lengthwise in half, then crosswise.
Carefully scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch of potato next to skin.
Arrange skins on serving plate. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread thin layer of sour cream in each shell.
Sprinkle with cheese, green onion and crumbled bacon. Microwave on Medium for 2 1/2 to 4 minutes, or until cheese melts, rotating plate after half the cooking time.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add squash to stuffing mixture and bake at 350° until heated.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until brown.
Drain.
Set aside. Arrange separated crescent rolls on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over and pick up sides to form crust.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle on potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper in bowl.
Pour over filling.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wild mushroom pasta(serves 4)
directions: In a large skillet, cook mushrooms, peppers and onion in hot margarine or butter until tender.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Toss with hot pasta.
Top with cheese.

title: taco casserole
directions: Fry beef and taco seasoning mix.
Then in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer first the bean dip, hamburger mixture, jalapeno peppers, sour cream and cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and stir into egg mixture.
Chill. Roll into balls (walnut size).
Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400° until light brown, but still soft.

title: chicken pie 1
directions: Remove chicken from bone; bring broth and soup to boil, cook until lumps are gone.
In bowl, mix melted margarine, flour, salt, pepper and buttermilk.
Pour soup over chicken in casserole dish, then pour batter mixture over this.
It makes its own crust when done.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: orange ice cream
directions: Note:
You may substitute Mountain Dew for Orange Crush.

title: flowerpot dirt pie
directions: You will need 1 clay flowerpot, 1 gardening hand shovel and 1 group of artificial flowers.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix the butter, sugar, and the eggs & vanilla, set aside.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning and water; mix well.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce. Spoon 1/2 bean mixture into pastry shell.
Top with 1/2 of meat mixture, 1/2 of cheese and all the chips.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomato.
Serves 6.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Mix together eggs, both sugars, vanilla and oil. Gradually stir in flour. Add pecans. Preheat oven to 325°. Bake 45 minutes. Center may be soft. Do not overbake.

title: leber kloes zoupa(liver dumpling soup)
directions: Place livers, onion and soda crackers through food grinder. Add beaten eggs, flour, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Mix well, drop by teaspoons into boiling chicken broth.
Cover and let simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: healthy wonder cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients. Add 1 cup water and stir well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes for 8-inch square pan. Bake 60 minutes for a tube pan.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix sugar, milk, nuts, margarine and coconut.
Form into balls.
Freeze.
In double boiler, melt together paraffin and chocolates.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and let set.

title: ham and sausage jambalaya
directions: In large heavy pot heat oil, add onion, pepper, celery, and garlic.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add ham and sausage, cook until sausage is light brown (8 minutes).
Add rice, cook 5 minutes-add tomatoes, beef broth and seasoning.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is reduced (about 45 minutes).
Add shrimp, simmer 5-10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and green onion.
Serve hot. (6-8 dinner size servings).

title: super stuffed pizza loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine picante sauce and tomato paste; mix well.
In large bowl, combine beef, sausage (no casing), 1/2 cup picante sauce mixture, onion, crumbs, egg and seasoning.
Mix well.
Divide in half.

title: chipped beef casserole
directions: Mix together in a greased casserole.
Let stand overnight or 4 to 5 hours.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate filled bars
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Add vanilla when melted.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into small pieces and cook 3 minutes in a small amount of water.
Saute onion and carrots in butter (tender, not brown).
Dissolve chicken bouillon cube in 1/4 cup boiling water and pour over squash.
Add cream of chicken soup and sour cream; mix all together.
Cover bottom of greased casserole with half of prepared dressing.
Add squash mixture.
Top with remaining dressing and bake at 350° to 375° until bubbling.

title: rice pudding deluxe
directions: Combine pineapple with liquid and instant pudding mix.
Stir well.
Add rice and marshmallows.
Add 1/2 cup pecans; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle remaining pecans on top.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: breakfast sausage seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes enough to season 5 pounds ground meat.
Pork, chicken, turkey and beef all work well, alone or in combination.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip ingredients together.
Serve chilled.
Best if refrigerated overnight.
Serve with fresh sliced fruit.

title: lemon broiled black cod
directions: Rinse fish with cold water.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Cut fish into 4 equal size serving portions. Set aside.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until done.

title: springerlief cookies
directions: Beat eggs 20 minutes on high until eggs change color (lighter).
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll out. Print (with springerlief boards or rolling pin) and cut apart.
Put in a cold room overnight. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 200 cookies. Store in an airtight container.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers, onions and celery; scald and let stand 5 minutes and drain.
Scald again and let stand 10 minutes; drain. Make syrup with vinegar, sugar and salt.
Put mustard and celery seeds in a small bag.
Put with syrup.
Put the syrup over the well drained mixture and boil slowly 20 minutes.
Pack in hot pints and seal.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: church supper potatoes
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and cook 1 hour at 375°. Uncover last few minutes and brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix buttermilk and baking soda in 2-cup measuring cup.
Cream butter with sugar until smooth; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add prepared buttermilk and soda mixture; stir.
Add flour mixed with salt; mix well.
Last, add bananas and nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Bake in loaf pans at 325° for about 1 hour or until done.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes (with all of the
other good things on top of it, of course!).
Makes a nice amount for pan pizza in a 10-inch skillet.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a quart jar.
Leave garlic in jar overnight and remove.

title: becky's mexican casserole
directions: Brown burger.
Dump in 3 cans and Tabasco (if desired). Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour into large microwavable casserole dish. Squoosh Tostitos on top.
Cover with cheeses.
Melt in microwave oven.
Dig in.

title: potato-bacon casserole
directions: Cook the bacon and drain. Break into pieces. Drain potatoes and put into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Add onion. Melt Velveeta in microwave. Add mayo and mix thoroughly. Stir gently into potatoes.
Put bacon pieces on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel desired amount of medium potatoes.
Put potato in large serving spoon and cut 1/8-inch to edge of spoon.
Do not cut through potato.
Put potatoes in cold water until through slicing. Dry potatoes and put in baking dish.
Pour a little Italian dressing over each potato.
Cook approximately 50 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash.
Add seasonings and beat until smooth and fluffy.
Refill whites of eggs.
Garnish with a dash of paprika.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Dice onions; saute.
In the meantime, blanche chopped cabbage in boiling water.
Strain cabbage; save the water.
Add cabbage to sauteed onions; add grated carrot for color.
Boil noodles and strain; add to cabbage when cabbage is soft.
Add little water (from cooking cabbage) to mixture to be of loose consistency. Season to taste.
bake in oven at 325°
for 15 minutes.

title: mama lola's chicken gumbo
directions: Place chicken in 5-quart Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add onion and garlic.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and cook slowly until chicken is tender.

title: coconut icebox pies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add water.
Cook to thin custard.
Add eggs (beaten) and marshmallows.
Cook until marshmallows melt. Remove from heat and add gelatin, softened in 1/3 cup water.
Cool in refrigerator; whip until fluffy.
Add 1 cup Milnot that has been whipped.
Add coconut, about 1/2 cup or more.
Fill 2 baked crusts and refrigerate.
When cool, top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Saute onion in oil; set aside.
Add meat; brown well on all sides.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Add broth and soup can of water, wine, pepper flakes and sauteed onion.
Bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat to serving platter.
Strain gravy, if desired.
Mix flour with remaining 1/3 cup water.
Gradually add to gravy.
Cook until thickened, stirring.
Blend in sour cream. Heat only until hot.
Spoon over beef cubes.
Serve with poppy seed noodles.
Makes 6 portions.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes. Take out and stir good with wire beater.
Repeat until mixture is as thick as you like.
Pour into pie shells and cool.
You may use your own meringue recipe.

title: copper penny (carrots)
directions: Cook the sliced carrots, then mix with sliced pepper and onions.
Mix the seasoning together.
Pour over the vegetables. Cover and let sit 24 hours in refrigerator.
Drain all the sauce off before serving.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: For each serving, spread salad dressing or mayonnaise and salsa on tortilla.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with lettuce and meat; roll up.
Wrap each tortilla in plastic wrap; refrigerate. I cut them about 1-inch thick and put toothpicks to hold them together.
Put on serving tray.

title: robbie's chocolate pie in microwave
directions: Heat 1 cup of milk with sugar in microwave.
Mix cocoa, salt, cornstarch, butter and 1/2 cup milk.
Add to heated milk.
Add well beaten egg yolks; smooth with wire whip.
Heat in microwave on High until bubbly.
Use whip to smooth.
Pour in pie shell when thick.
Add meringue and bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: applets
directions: Combine 1 envelope of gelatin with 1/2 cup apples.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine lemon juice, 3/4 cup apples, sugar and gelatin.
Add to first mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 15 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into an oiled 8-inch pan.
Let stand 24 hours in fridge.
Cut into small pieces.
Roll in powdered sugar and cornstarch mixture.
Let dry, uncovered, until outside has dried.

title: dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Let cool.
Prepare jello and let cool.
Punch holes in cake with fork and pour cooled jello over it.
Mix cream cheese with Cool Whip and spread on cake. Chill until ready to serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Make cream sauce of butter, flour, salt and milk.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: night before casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or 6 to 12 hours.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Take cover off last few minutes.
(Can be cut in half for smaller families.)

title: banana bread (loaf)
directions: Beat shortening until creamy (1 minute at medium speed on mixer).
Blend in sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with bananas.
Blend well.
Grease bottom of a 4 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Turn batter into pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack.

title: come back sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in heavy pan and simmer slowly for two hours.
Stir occasionally.
Put into hot sterilized pint jars. Seal.
Yields seven pints.

title: bread pudding a la bon ton
directions: Place bread and raisins in buttered baking dish.
Bring milk to a boil in another pan.
Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla in a bowl. Pour milk over the egg mixture and stir thoroughly.
Pour over bread and raisins.
Dot with butter and bake at 300° until firm, about 1 hour.

title: greek spinach and cheese turnovers
directions: In blender or mixer, combine egg, onion and Feta cheese; beat. Add cream cheese; combine well.
Add spinach and seasonings.
Mix until blended.
Chill 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Beat into 3 slightly beaten eggs.
Add 4 cups (1-inch slices) rhubarb (about 1 pound).
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry. Fill with mixture.
Dot with 2 cubes butter; top with lattice crust.
Flute edge.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 50 to 60 minutes; cool.

title: pepper steak
directions: Take bite size steak; flour it and put into skillet with a little oil.
Brown halfway.
Add onion, pepper, salt and garlic salt; finish browning.
Add water.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Add mushroom soup.
Serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: sylvia's 2-egg coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add and beat in the eggs. Add and beat the milk and vanilla.
Add and beat the flour and baking powder.
Pour into buttered pan and bake in 375° oven until brown.
This is the Basic Recipe For All Cakes.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in greased loaf pan.
Serve with turkey gravy (chicken can be used).

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix and bake at 375° until pie is firm.

title: j l h chunky tomato soup
directions: Saute onion in a bit of butter.
Set aside.
Mix bacon fat (amount is optional) with onion and butter.
In a large saucepan, combine the soup, milk, tomatoes and seasonings.
Heat on medium, stirring often.
Add some of the soup to the bacon fat and blend. Stir this into the pot of soup.
Continue heating but do not boil. Stir often.
Add bacon.
Makes 6 to 7 cups.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and egg; add nuts, flour and apples. Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° until brown.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Mix sugars, peanut butter, shortening, margarine and eggs. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add a little flour if it is too sticky to make into a ball.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Leave in a ball.
Bake until golden brown, 9 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately place unwrapped chocolate kiss in the middle.
Makes about 5 or 6 dozen cookies.

title: fudge topped brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine margarine, sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, eggs, milk and 1 1/2 tsp. vanilla; beat well.
Stir in nuts if desired.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of the pan.
Just before brownies are done, in heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and remaining 1 1/2 tsp. vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Immediately spread over hot brownies.
Cool.
Chill. Cut into bars.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients (except poppy seed) together until well blended.
Add 1/4 cup poppy seed.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 regular sized or 3 smaller sized loaves.

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in rapidly boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain and rinse with cold water.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add shrimp, garlic and mushrooms; cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add spaghetti to the skillet; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Toss in skillet until spaghetti is hot, but do not let margarine brown.
Turn onto warm serving dish; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Garnish with sprigs of parsley for color, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: crabmeat puffs
directions: Combine soft cream cheese, milk, horseradish, salt and pepper. Mix well until blended.
Add crabmeat, nuts and onion.
Mix well.
Fill miniature cream puffs with crabmeat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cut carrots in lengthwise strips or use the canned carrots. Cook until just tender, about 15 to 20 minutes. Place in a shallow baking dish. Mix other ingredients and pour over carrots. Top with bread crumbs or Pepperidge Farm herb dressing (1/4 cup), 1 tablespoon butter and dash of paprika. (May also sprinkle with parsley.) Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and Kool-Aid in hot water.
Add cold water. Freeze in small paper cups or muffin tins.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt;
place
in
a nonstick baking pan, skin side down.
Combine
water, juice, lemon peel, thyme and marjoram; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes,
basting with
pan
liquid.
Turn	chicken
over; continue baking and basting
30 minutes more, until chicken is cooked through and skin
is crispy.
Remove chicken;
sprinkle with paprika and garnish with lemon wedges and parsley.

title: blackberry pudding
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, berries, flour and cloves. Mix well.
Bake in buttered baking dish at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased).
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Flour and brown chicken in olive oil.
Put in a pan.
Add the rest of the ingredients and bake at 350° until chicken is done (about 1 hour).

title: heavenly fudge pie
directions: Crust:
Mix crumbs and margarine, press to bottom and sides of 9-inch pie shell, bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: vesta's dressing for cole slaw
directions: Mix all in blender and serve over chopped cabbage.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Let dough rise.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Add melted butter to all ingredients (except dough). Spray pan.
Add nuts and raisins on bottom of pan.
Pull dough apart; lay on top of nuts.
Pour mixed ingredients over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Invert buns on foil when done. Foil should be larger than pan.

title: freezer corn
directions: Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Cook in pans completely.
Put in freezer bags.

title: creamy chocolate candy
directions: Mix water, chocolate chips and syrup.
Melt in double boiler. Add peanuts, raisins or marshmallows.
Form into balls on wax paper.
Chill.

title: cheese straws
directions: Have cheese and oleo at room temperature.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Put through cheese straw press onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Cut into 4-inch pieces before cooking or break after cooking.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until dried out, but not brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Combine all ingredients except carrots.
Pour sauce over carrots that have been placed in dish.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Serve hot or cold.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Thoroughly combine completely thawed strawberries and syrup with dry gelatin; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Pour batter evenly over marshmallows in pan.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown and toothpick comes out clean.
As the cake bakes, the strawberries sink and the marshmallows rise and glaze the top.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugars and vanilla until creamy. Stir in nuts.
Slice Granny Smith and Red Delicious apples and dip.

title: caramel-chocolate squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat caramels and 1/4 cup of milk in saucepan, stirring constantly, until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth. Keep mixture warm over low heat.
Mix cake mix (dry), margarine, remaining milk and nuts.
Spread 1/2 of the dough in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes; remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and coconut over baked layer. Drizzle caramel mixture over chips.
Drop remaining dough by teaspoonfuls onto caramel layer.
Bake until cake is slightly dry to touch (15 to 20 minutes).
Cool.
Refrigerate until firm and cut into squares.

title: hearty hamburger stew
directions: Place onions, carrots, green pepper and mushrooms in butter. Add meat and cook until crumbly.
Drain off grease.
Stir in juice, potatoes and seasoning.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and 1 cup of milk, beat until smooth. Stir into soup.
Add remaining milk.
Heat and stir.

title: rhubarb squares
directions: Pat first 6 ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Place rhubarb over that mixture and sprinkle the Jell-O from the package on last.
Mix the last 3 ingredients as for pie crust and sprinkle over Jell-O.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
It is good warm with ice cream or cut into bars.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: In a large pot, add approximately
gallon or more of water. Add salt and bring to a boil; break spaghetti at least 2 times and add to boiling water.
Stir
with
a fork.
Do not overcook; drain and rinse well.
Let	cool.
Add
all
of
the ingredients. Let set overnight and serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until tender.
Transfer to large mixing bowl and add other ingredients.
Blend well.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 11-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top begins to brown.

title: wok shrimp
directions: Heat oil in wok to 375°.
Cook the vegetables in sequence. As they are done, push up on sides of wok.

title: cheesecake
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl.
With mixer beat at high speed 5 to 10 minutes until thick and creamy.
Pour mixture into a snap ring pan and place in center of preheated 200° oven.
When cake rises 1/4 inch out of pan, open oven door; keep heat on.
Let cake settle.
When settled, close door.
Open again when cake peaks second time.
When it settles, close door, turn heat to 375° and let it rise and brown.
It's done when it is 1/2 inch above the pan.
Place on cooling rack and add powdered sugar.

title: ham quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Sprinkle bacon and onion on bottom of crust. Add half of ham, 4 slices of cheese, rest of ham and then cheese. Beat eggs and mustard. Add hot cream; beat. Pour over ham and cheese. Let stand 10 minutes. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until custard is set.

title: wedding punch(the best!)
directions: Blend strawberries with sugar and a little of the Sprite in blender until smooth. Mix all other ingredients with this in a gallon container. Makes 1 gallon. Freeze until slushie. Serve.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange the first 4 ingredients in layers in a flat bowl. Spread Miracle Whip over the peas.
Sprinkle with sugar. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Garnish with shredded cheese, slices of hard-boiled egg and crumbled bacon just before serving.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese and Velveeta cheese.
Mix and whip until fluffy.
Add pepper, garlic powder and nuts.
Shape into logs and roll in chili powder.
Refrigerate.

title: dessert waffles
directions: Whip the cream until stiff.
In another bowl, beat eggs until light.
Fold in cream.
Fold in the flour, salt and sugar, then the hot melted butter.
Heat the waffle iron and brush with shortening.
Pour in batter.
Cook until golden brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Beat well. Add eggs and blend. Sift dry ingredients twice and add nuts to dry ingredients. Blend thoroughly with other mixture. Add carrots a small amount at a time and blend well. Turn into 3 paper-lined cake pans. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool thoroughly.

title: special layered salad
directions: In a 3-quart bowl, layer the lettuce, green pepper, onion, peas, mayonnaise and cheese. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Soak zucchini 1 1/2 hours in ice water; do not peel.
Beat eggs on high speed until thick.
Mix 3 1/4 cups flour; add other dry ingredients.
Dredge raisins and nuts with remaining 1/4 cup flour.
Mix into eggs on low speed, fold in other ingredients. Add vanilla.
Grease 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3 1/2-inch.
Line with wax paper.
Bake in middle of a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes. Freezes well.

title: jiffy corn muffins
directions: Blend ingredients; batter will be slightly lumpy.
For maximum crown on muffins, let batter rest for 3 to 4 minutes before filling cups.
Fill muffin cups half full.
Preheat oven to 400°. Grease muffin pans or use paper baking cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add egg yolks and melted chocolate. Then add vanilla, flour, soda, baking powder and buttermilk; mix well.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked hamburgers
directions: Shape hamburgers into patties and pour the sauce over.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until done at 350° or 375°.
Some ovens vary in temperature.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add flour.
Slowly add milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Boil potatoes until tender and drain.
Put potatoes into 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Add mustard and mayo to cream sauce.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cut margarine into dry ingredients in a food processor.
Add beaten egg at the last minute.
Wrap dough in plastic and chill. Roll dough between two pieces of waxed paper about 1/8-inch thick. Cut with pizza cutter or knife into straws about 14 x 2-inches. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: yeast bread - no knead
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Add 1 1/4 cups flour and beat well.
Add yeast and egg and beat.
Add remaining flour.
Place in greased bowl and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours (doubled).
Shape dough and let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until meat wants to fall apart.
Make up Stove Top stuffing after meat has cooled.
Pull apart and put a layer in large greased baking dish.
Mix together cream of chicken, Miracle Whip and cheese soup.
Pour 1/2 over chicken; add a layer of Stove Top.
Repeat layer, ending with Stove Top on top. Bake in oven set at 350° for 1 hour or until sauce bubbles through the Stove Top.
Serves hot.

title: baked salmon with cheese stuffing
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender, 7 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and mix. Layer the mix in a 1.5-quart loaf pan (Pyrex), starting with the mix, then the salmon. Top with sliced almonds. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bert's favorite pepper steak
