directions: Slice steak into thin strips, place in large skillet with the heated oil and cook on high about 5 minutes or until done.
Add water, onions (sliced in rings) and garlic salt.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Cut bell pepper in large pieces.
Add to skillet and simmer 5 more minutes. Mix cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce; stir into meat mixture. Stir until thick, about 2 minutes.
Cut tomatoes into wedges; place on top, cover and heat for 3 minutes.
Turn off; serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in a glass container. Place in refrigerator.
This goes well with carrots, cauliflower florets, celery or sliced cucumbers.
This is also excellent as a salad dressing.

title: oven-steamed rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart ungreased casserole with tight fitting lid, combine all ingredients.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes (don't peek; don't stir).
To serve, fluff up lightly with a fork.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain grease.
Add onions, barbecue sauce, mushrooms, mustard, pepper and garlic powder. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
In separate pan, fry bacon until crisp; drain grease.
Crumble bacon into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients (including beans) and put in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 1 hour.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Put oil into skillet and ground chuck with onions and brown. Drain oil off.
Add Sloppy Joe mix.
Stir real good.
Add all of remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes or longer.
If it gets thick, just add a little water and cook longer.

title: pie dessert
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; stir in sugar.
Fold in crumbs and nuts.
Pour into well-greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream and grated chocolate.

title: grilled chicken and pasta(yield:  4-6 servings)
directions: 1. Marinate chicken breasts in 3 oz. salad dressing for at least 2 hours.

title: mom's chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in mold and refrigerate overnight.
This will congeal.
May be used for salad or dessert.

title: midget chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Then add oil, water and vinegar.
In your mini cupcake pan, place mini cupcake liners.
Fill liners 1/2 full with chocolate batter. Now mix together the 4 oz. cream cheese, egg and 1/6 cup sugar. Place 1/2 tsp. of cream cheese batter on top of the chocolate batter in liners.
Top with miniature chocolate chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 18 minutes.
Let cool and refrigerate.
Make 4 1/2 dozen.

title: easy pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, oil and flour to form a soft dough.
Add more flour as needed.
Let rest.
Divide dough and press out on two greased pizza pans.
Cover with sauce and toppings.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green beans and burger
directions: Cook beef and onions until brown; drain.
Add seasonings, 1/2 cheese and rice.
Place in baking dish.
Top with green beans. Blend together the soup, milk, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over beans; sprinkle with other 1/2 of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple crescent cookies
directions: Blend and mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Mix until dough holds together.
Chill.
Combine nuts, pineapple preserves and enough cream to moisten.
Roll and cut dough.
Put in preserves. Roll in crescent.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all but potatoes and bacon together in skillet; stir in 1 cup water and 1/4 cup vinegar.
Cook until it boils; boil 1 minute.
Pour over potatoes and bacon.
Serve.

title: turkey and stuffing pie
directions: Press stuffing into bottom and sides of well-greased 9-inch pie plate. Top with turkey and cheese. Beat eggs and milk; pour over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: mustard topped cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Place the cauliflower head in a large casserole with 1/4 cup water.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain the water off.
Mix the mayonnaise, chopped onion and mustard; spoon over the cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Microwave on 3/4 power for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese, cream cheese, mayonnaise and egg together.
Roll each slice of bread flat.
Spread cheese mixture on slices.
Top with 1 stalk asparagus.
Roll up.
Cut in half or thirds.
Brush on melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until well browned.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Makes about 50.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all together and stir well.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add to rhubarb in prepared 10-inch pie pan. Cover with lattice strips.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from bone.
In bottom of dish, layer chicken, chips (crushed), onion, bell pepper and cheese.
Pour 1/2 cup broth over this.
Repeat layers.
Mix together soup, tomatoes and chili powder.
Pour over chicken layer. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and soup gets hot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well and pour into graham pie crust and chill.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in a greased casserole.
Add salt, lemon juice and water.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon, flour and butter together until crumblike consistency.
Spread this over the apples.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine the beef, onion, bread crumbs, egg, salt, black pepper and 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Form into a loaf and place it in a shallow pan.

title: mediterranean seafood casserole
directions: Slice potatoes thinly and cook in 1 inch boiling water until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain and reserve.
Cut some in chunks and add garlic, onion, bell pepper, stewed tomato liquid, bay leaf, basil and thyme.
Bring to a boil, reduce and simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms, zucchini, stewed tomatoes and 4 tablespoons of the parsley.
Recover and simmer 6 minutes. Remove and discard bay leaf.

title: old fashion strawberry shortcake
directions: Grease and flour the bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Mix ingredients with a spoon until well blended.
Pour into the pan and spread the mixture, which is fairly stiff.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour.
Bake longer if you desire a darker crust.

title: quick cracker crunch
directions: Melt sugar and butter over medium heat until bubbly; cook 4 minutes.
Mix in pecans and pour over layer of crackers.
Bake at 400°.
Cut into strips.

title: old fashion chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken, celery, salt, eggs and pickles.
Moisten with mayonnaise and chill.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except onions) in a 2-quart casserole. Top with onion rings.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Serve with cranberry sauce. Serves 6.
Delicious.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion.
Mix.
Let stand 10 minutes until liquid rises to top.
Drain. Stir in eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Heat well-greased skillet on medium heat. Drop by tablespoon into skillet. Brown 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve warm.

title: aunt alice's red velvet cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix.
Dissolve cocoa in food coloring.
Combine buttermilk, salt and vanilla.
Add alternately with cake flour to the creamed mixture.
Last fold in (by hand) the soda that has been dissolved in the vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 layers, using regular 8-inch pans.

title: meat casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into square baking dish.
Spread crumbs and melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In
mixing bowl, stir together first five ingredients.
Add shortening, egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in oats.
Form into small balls.
Dip tops in additional sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and bell pepper together and drain. Mix all ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, vanilla, egg, sour milk, baking soda and salt well.
Add rhubarb pieces; mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with brown sugar and nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
"Enjoy with Cool Whip."

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Bring all ingredients except onion, bell pepper and cabbage to a boil.
Pour over cabbage, onion and pepper.
Will keep several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving 1/4 of the beef to roll the ball in.
Put in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix and pour in crumb crust and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix applesauce, egg and melted butter.
Pour all at once into dry mixture.
Stir just until moist.
Pour batter into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: susan's quick dinner
directions: Brown beef until cooked through.
Drain well.
Add the rest of the ingredients except water.
Cook uncovered on medium heat until tomatoes are soft and cooked into a sauce.
Add water to keep the mixture from getting too thick, usually about 1/4 to 1/2 cup of water.
Serve over white rice.

title: olive green beans
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan.
Drain green beans and add butter; heat.
Season to taste; dash with nutmeg.
Add olives. Makes 4 servings.

title: planters holiday nuts 'n spice cookies(makes about 6 dozen)
directions: Finely chop 1 1/2 cups nuts.
Combine flour, chopped nuts and baking powder; set aside.
In saucepan, heat sugar, molasses, water, allspice and cinnamon to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine until melted.
Blend in flour mixture.
Chill 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Add 4 cooked chicken breasts.
Mix in soup and mayonnaise.
Butter casserole dish and fill with ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° (about 30 minutes) until contents bubble and brown.

title: bucky's "after a time" macaroni soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown onion.
Add ground chuck.
Cook until crumbly.
Add tomato sauce and equal amount of water; bring to a boil.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Cook pasta and drain.
Add to soup and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients mixing well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until pie sets.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place thawed dough on lightly floured surface and roll out to 13-inch circle.
Transfer to a 12-inch pizza pan.
Trim excess dough, leaving a 1-inch border extending over pan edges.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden; let cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, orange peel and vanilla well together. Spread over cooled cookie.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese mixture.
Brush fruit with lemon juice.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours. Serves 8 to 12.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Place butter and onions in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble beef into butter and onions.
Cook together.
Drain excess grease. Add beef, broth, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and steak sauce.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce, dissolve jello in hot sauce.
Do not use any water.
Mix until well dissolved.
Chill until beginning to thicken and add rest of ingredients.
Chill until completely set.

title: nut logs
directions: Cut together 2 cups flour and 1/2 pound margarine.
Add 1 egg yolk and 3/4 cup sour cream.
Mix well and wrap in wax paper. Chill in freezer a few hours to get it cold.
Roll into 3 oblong shapes (as if making sweet rolls).
Mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over dough.
(Use more flour to roll dough if it sticks.)

title: ellen's chili
directions: Brown together ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.

title: mom's sawdust pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.
Serve warm with Cool Whip and sliced fruit to garnish.
Yummy!

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Prepare and cook broccoli.
Heat remaining ingredients over medium heat, stirring frequently until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth, 6 to 8 minutes.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hoe cakes
directions: In a medium bowl, mix 1 tablespoon of drippings with remaining ingredients.
Preheat a cast-iron skillet over medium heat.
Add remaining 4 tablespoons of the bacon drippings or shortening to the skillet.
Drop round cakes of the cornmeal batter, approximately 1 or 1 1/2-inches thick, into the skillet. Fry 1 or 2 minutes or until golden on each side.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.

title: pigs-in-a-blanket
directions: Season generously strips of round steak with salt, pepper, garlic salt and onion salt.
Place piece of bacon on each strip (or cook bacon first and place on each strip of meat; it is just a little tricky rolling up the meat with cooked bacon).
Roll up strips of meat and bacon and secure with toothpicks.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
In small skillet, melt margarine.
Add green pepper and onion.
Saute until crisp-tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour uncovered at 350° until golden and bubbly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend together margarine, sugar and egg.
Add flour.
Stir in banana and nuts.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spider legs
directions: Melt chips.
When melted, stir in noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: chicken continental(chicken and rice)
directions: Roll chicken in seasoned flour.
Saute in butter until tender. Mix soup, onion and seasonings in a pan. Gradually stir in water. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour rice into a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Stir all except 1/3 cup soup mixture into rice. Top with chicken.
Pour on remaining soup mixture. Cover and bake in oven at 375° for about 30 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll to size of small walnut, please, with a fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar on top.
Freezes well.

title: tofu teriyaki steak
directions: Cut tofu crosswise into thirds; then cut into halves.
Prepare Teriyaki Sauce with the remaining ingredients.
Marinate tofu in Teriyaki Sauce for 20 to 30 minutes.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in 12-inch skillet over medium heat; add tofu pieces and stir-fry until golden brown on both sides.
Repeat until all tofu is stir-fried.
Sprinkle 7-Spice powder and chopped green onion if you desire.

title: blue ribbon chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine flour, salt and soda; mix well. Set aside.
In large bowl, blend sugars at medium speed.
Add butter and mix to form a paste.
Add eggs and extract. Mix at medium speed until blended.
Do not overmix.
Add flour mix and chips.
Blend at low speed until just mixed.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Transfer to cool surface with spatula immediately.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven at 325° for 1 hour or more.
Beat sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon slowly.
Mix well with mixer until creamy.
Add apples and nuts and mix with spoon until everything is mixed well.
Bake; serve warm.
Good cold, too.

title: banana shake
directions: Put the bananas in the blender and mash them. Add the other ingredients. Mix until slightly frothy. Makes 8 1/2 cup servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove any skin, bones or fat. Tear in medium size pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: plum pudding
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Make hole in middle.
Drain plum juice in hole.
Add eggs; mix well.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo, soda and water to dissolve soda.
Add the chopped nuts and plums. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar, soda and salt.
Cream dry mixture with shortening. Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to shortening mixture alternately with flour.
Do all mixing by hand.
Chill overnight. Roll out.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Melt butter in 1/4 cup boiling water; add flour and dash of salt and stir well.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball; remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add egg; beat until smooth and stir in cheese.
Drop dough onto greased baking sheet using 1 level teaspoon dough to each puff; bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.
Remove puffs from oven; cool and split.
Combine remaining ingredients, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; fill each puff with 2 teaspoons.

title: ramen noodle shrimp salad
directions: Boil noodles 3 minutes; drain.
Mix 3 of the dry seasoning packages with mayonnaise.
Add to drained noodles.
Add vegetables and shrimp.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Arrange potatoes in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Layer beans over top.
Drain fish on paper towel.
Place fish over beans and sprinkle with salt.
In bowl, combine soup, cheese, parsley and lemon rind.
Spoon mixture over fish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with tomato slices.
Return to oven and bake 10 more minutes.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: frozen coleslaw
directions: Use ground turkey instead of ground beef.

title: vyrla's fudge brownies
directions: Cream together the sugar and margarine.
Add the rest, one by one, while beating each ingredient in.
Pour into cake pan sprayed with Pam (a 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Take out of oven while toothpick is still sticky if you want them fudgy like.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of double boiler. Place over hot water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix. Spread candy in a buttered pan.
Cool and cut in squares.
Yields 2 dozen pieces.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Boil jello, pineapple and sugar.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate until set.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Crust:
Mix 1 cup Bisquick and 1/4 cup water.
Knead lightly and press into pie or quiche pan.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set in middle.
Recipe doubles easily for large crowd.

title: quick cocoa cake icing
directions: Bring
to
boil cocoa and oleo;
add sugar and vanilla. Spread over cake while hot.

title: curried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces small enough to saute easily in about an hour.
Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add curry and stir. Add 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in garlic, ginger, salt, chili and tomato.
Cook until tomato is slightly soft.
Add more warm water if needed.
Add chicken, one piece at a time and coat with curry sauce.
Add more warm water when all chicken pieces are in.
It should be approximately 1 to 2 cups.
Turn and simmer chicken, cooking on low heat about an hour until done.
Before serving, add chopped coriander.
Serve over rice or nan.

title: angel food cake (fat free-low calorie)
directions: Be sure egg whites are at room temperature.
This takes about 1 hour.
Sift flour and powdered sugar together 3 times.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, evaporated milk, 1 stick butter, and vanilla and pour into buttered casserole.
Mix pecans, flour, brown sugar, and 1 stick melted butter; spread on top of casserole mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; spread over a plate.
Spread chili sauce over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle crab meat over sauce and top with shredded parsley.
Scoop with crackers.

title: hearty oat bread(special diet, low-fat and no eggs)
directions: *Do not decrease amount of salt, necessary to rise adequately.

title: squash pickle relish
directions: Soak squash in 3 quarts of water with salt for 1 hour.
Drain, but do not wash.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven at 425°.
Remove skin from chicken.
Split breasts.
Place chicken in ungreased baking pan.
Spread 1 teaspoon soft butter or margarine on the chicken pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 45 minutes until tender.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley. Serves 2.
Calories per serving: 225.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into muffin tins and bake at 350° until brown.

title: french apple pie
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Add melted margarine and beaten egg; mix well.
Add apples.
Place in unbaked pie shell; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Cook until thick:
brown sugar, water, rhubarb and cornstarch or flour.
Stir butter, flour, oatmeal and cinnamon into crumbs. (May use pastry blender.)
Place a layer of crumbs in bottom of pan.
(Save a little for the top.)
Cut rhubarb (raw) in about 1-inch pieces over layer of crumbs.
Add cooked mixture.
Sprinkle saved crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creole green beans
directions: Cut the beans in half crosswise and then lengthwise (as for French-cut beans).
Place in large saucepan.
Add water to cover. Bring to a boil and cook, covered, until beans are tender.
Drain and return beans to the pot.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Put jello in blender.
Pour in boiling pear syrup plus water to make one cup and blend.
With blender on, add chunks of cream cheese and pears.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate until set. Blend in whipped cream (or Cool Whip) and pour into mold.
Serves about 8.
Especially good with grilled chicken.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first seven ingredients.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into a loaf and place into a greased loaf pan or casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour; drain grease.
Top with ketchup or warm picante sauce.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and sausage; drain off all fat.
Chop tomatoes and drain. Chop peppers and drain. Remove seeds from jalapeno peppers. Cut cheese into small pieces.
Add all other ingredients to cooked mixture and cook until cheese melts.

title: orange brandied sweet potato casserole*
directions: Boil, peel and mash sweet potatoes.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Continue beating and add orange juice slowly until of mashed potato consistency.
Add brown sugar to sweeten. Add brandy.
Put in casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
(This can be prepared the day before and reheated.)

title: spring spinach salad
directions: Wash and stem spinach.
Crisp in ice water.
Dry.
Tear into enough bite size pieces to make 3 cups.
Put into salad bowl with eggs and onions.

title: poor man's cobbler
directions: *Peaches, strawberries or blueberries can be used.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours with sliced, cooked beef, pork or chicken or a combination of cooked meats.
Serve on a kaiser roll or hamburger bun.

title: cheese ball
directions: In food processor fitted with steel blade or mixer, combine all ingredients except chilies and walnuts.
Blend thoroughly. Stir in chilies.
Divide mixture into thirds.
Chill 15 to 20 minutes.
Press each into walnuts.
Press each into molds lined with plastic wrap, or shape into balls.
Cover with plastic wrap. Chill 1 hour or overnight.

title: homemade souse
directions: Mix all ingredients (hog head should be taken off the bone and cut or mashed well).
Put into cheesecloth and mash grease out. Tie up and hang up overnight to drip.
Take out of cloth, slice thin and store in refrigerator.

title: wheat salad
directions: Wash wheat and soak in water overnight.
Cook 2 hours or until crunchy soft.
Drain and cool.
In large bowl, soften cream cheese.
Add pudding (dry) and stir.
Add pineapple with enough juice to make a batter.
Fold in the topping.
Add cold wheat and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook eggs and set aside.
In wok or large iron skillet at high heat, spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add onion and cook about 1 1/2 minutes, then add bean sprouts.
Keep stirring, then add the rice and soy sauce.
Fold into onion and bean sprouts. The rice should have a light brown color.
Stir until blended, then fold in egg.
Remove from heat and toss with green onion.

title: night before omelet
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and place in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan which has been greased.
Cover and refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: ash reshte(vegetable soup with noodles)
directions: Combine water, spinach, cilantro, parsley, green onions and dill in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and let simmer for 20 minutes.
Add lentils, pinto beans and garbanzos to the soup.
Let it simmer for 5 minutes.
Make sure there is enough water covering the ingredients.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes or until well done.
Add milk and next 4 ingredients.
Gradually add enough instant potato flakes to make soup as thick as you like.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with thyme sprigs if desired.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Stir strawberries and sugar in a bowl.
Bring water and pectin to a boil.
Let boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add pectin mixture to strawberries and stir 3 minutes. Pour into 1/2 pint jars, one inch from top.
Put cap on and screw top on tight.
Set at room temperature for 24 hours.
Place in freezer.

title: chicken fettuccine(low-fat recipe)
directions: Spray a large nonstick frying pan with nonfat cooking spray. Saute the onion and garlic in chicken broth.
Add the basil and other seasonings.
Add chicken and saute about 7 minutes or until the chicken is cooked.
Add the zucchini and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Add the fettuccine and milk.
Sprinkle the cheese on top and mix well.
Yields 6 to
8 servings.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Blend cheese with mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce. Add green peppers, onion and salt and pepper to taste. Makes about 12 sandwiches.

title: melon salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 2 hours.

title: emerald salad
directions: Heat liquid and dissolve gelatin in liquid.
Allow gelatin to set.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.

title: marbled pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Crust:
In a medium bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press onto bottom of greased 10-inch spring-form pan; sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate chips.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Spray a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with Pam, or else grease it.
Mix the above; pat into the pan, making sure that you cover the bottom and part way up the sides.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cut onions into thick slices.
Melt butter in heavy pan.
Add onions and sugar; cook, stirring, until the onions are golden brown and transparent.
Stir flour in gradually until blended. Stir in stock, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. While soup is cooking, slice bread into thick slices and toast.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Line baked shell with 2 cups raw berries.
Cook remaining berries with remaining ingredients, except butter.
Add butter when mixture is thick.
Pour over berries in pie shell.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, beat 1 1/4 cups sugar, shortening and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, then bananas. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda and beat into the sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Chill 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar/cinnamon mixture over cookies.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until light brown. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: hershey pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add cocoa alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Gradually fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: french-style chicken
directions: Mix dressing, onion soup, cranberry sauce and raisins in a bowl.
Pour over chicken and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serves about 6 to 8.

title: irish cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Bottle and refrigerate. Stir each time before using. No waiting. Can be served as soon as it's chilled.

title: chocolate cream delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix first three ingredients together in large glass baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool this layer.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into four rectangles. Press to seal perforations.
Place 8 pepperoni slices on each. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Start with short side and roll up each rectangle.
Pinch and seal.
Slice each roll into 4 equal slices.
Pinch dough on one side of each slice to seal. Place sealed side down on ungreased sheet.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields 16 servings.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate with solid shortening or butter. Press thawed hash browns between paper toweling to remove excess moisture.
Fit hash browns into pie plate, cutting and trimming to make a solid crust.
Brush hash brown crust with melted butter; be sure to brush top edges, too.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven; fill with layers of cheese and ham.
Beat cream with eggs and seasoned salt; pour over cheese and ham.
Return to oven.
Reduce heat; bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes, or until knife inserted near edge comes out clean.

title: the best pecan pie
directions: Stir together corn syrup, sugar, eggs, lemon juice, vanilla, salt and chopped pecans.
Blend in cooled butter.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Stir in potato chips and mix well.
Stir in flour just until dough pulls away from the side of the bowl and forms a ball.
Shape into 1 inch balls; place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets. Flatten with glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 350 for 12-15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sponge candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and vinegar in heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking without stirring to 310° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in soda.
Mix well.
Pour in buttered 9-inch pan.
Cover with melted chocolate when cooled.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove the stem, seeds and membrane of the bell peppers.
Wash inside and out.
Cover with boiling water; cook 3 to 5 minutes. Drain and cut in half crosswise.

title: mediterranean chicken thighs
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Use large frypan to heat oil to medium-high.
Add thighs, skin down; cook until brown (5 minutes).
Turn thighs.
Add onions, garlic and mushrooms; cook for 5 minutes.

title: irene's pie crust(never fails)
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add ice water to hold ingredients together, mixing to form ball.
Roll approximately 1/8-inch thick on floured board. Fits into an 8 to 9-inch pie pan.
Fill.

title: saucy pizza rolls
directions: Cook lasagna noodles; drain and cool.
Preheat oven to 350°. In a skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in 1/4 cup pizza sauce, 1/2 cup cheese, mushrooms and egg.
Spread each lasagna noodle with 1/3 cup of meat mixture.
Carefully roll up and place seam down in an ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over rolls.
Cover and bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake an additional 4 to 6 minutes to melt cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in halves and remove seeds. Place each half on a double thickness of aluminum foil. Put teaspoon of butter and brown sugar in each half. Add mixture of apples and walnuts. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and wrap securely in foil. Barbecue on grill about one hour, turning once. Squash is done when it feels soft when touched.

title: tuna roll-ups
directions: Cook peas and onion in margarine.
Stir in half can undiluted soup.
Fold in tuna.
Set aside.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together milk and sugar and melt, then add flour.
Pour peaches on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pat out in pie plate with your hands.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: cheese stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients with 1 egg.
Combine remaining egg with the next 3 ingredients.
Press 1/3 meat mixture into 9-inch loaf pan.
Make a well.
Spoon in cheese.
Cover with remaining meat.
Pat firmly at sides.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry desert
directions: Mix all ingredients together
in 9 x 13 pan and bake at 400°.
Stir every 5 minutes until mixture is browned and crumbly.
IMPORTANT! IF YOU DO NOT STIR EVERY 5 MINUTES, MIXTURE WILL DEFINITELY BURN! It should take 20 - 25 minutes total.
Remove 1/4 of mixture. Spread remaining mixture over bottom of pan.
Set all aside to cool.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: In saucepan, combine ingredients.
Heat slowly until sugar lumps disappear.
Cool in pan until completely cool.
Turn out on cake plate.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters; save liquid.
Heat milk gradually.
Add butter, Worcestershire sauce, oyster juice, salt and pepper.
Set aside. Layer 1/3 of saltines on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 of eggs and 1/2 of oysters.
Layer 1/3 of saltines.
Pour 1/2 liquid over layers.
Layer remaining eggs and oysters.
Pour remaining liquid over layers.
Top with remaining saltines.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or until crusty on top.

title: best banana bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(You may add 1 1/2 cups chopped nuts.)

title: double chocolate walnut brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a medium-size pan over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Beat in sugar gradually with a wooden spoon until thoroughly combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition; stir in vanilla.
Stir in flour until thoroughly combined.
Stir in one cup of walnuts.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine remaining 1/2 cup of walnuts with chocolate pieces. Sprinkle over top of brownie mixture, pressing down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top springs back lightly with fingertip.
Cool completely in pan or on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine corn syrup, eggs, sugar, butter and salt.
Beat until blended.
Beat in melted chocolate.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake on lower rack of preheated 375° oven, until filling is completely puffed across top and crusted over, 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In large pot, add tomato juice, frozen vegetables, corned beef, garlic and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat to a simmer.

title: tender chunk ham casserole
directions: Flake apart ham with a fork.
Heat together soup, milk, Cheddar cheese, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add flaked ham.
Add this mixture to cooked, drained macaroni.
Top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sirloin steak with onion-mustard sauce
directions: In a heavy skillet, heat 2 tablespoons olive oil over medium heat.
Add steak and saute for 2 or 3 minutes on each side if you would like it medium rare and 5 minutes on each side for well done. Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with pepper and set aside in a covered dish.

title: four egg cake
directions: Blend
sugar
and
butter or margarine until creamy and light. Beat
in
egg
yolks,
one at a time.
Add vanilla. Resift flour
with
baking
powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.	Add these to butter mixture with milk and beat until smooth.
Beat egg
whites until
stiff;
add	1/4
teaspoon salt.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Bake
in 3 greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use frosting of your choice.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Meanwhile, lightly brown garlic in hot oil.
Remove from heat and add parsley, pepper, salt, clams with juice and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until heated through.
Pour over hot pasta and toss.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potato latkes
directions: Slice desired number of potatoes onto heavy aluminum foil. Slice 1/2 to 1 onion on top.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons butter or margarine, salt and pepper.
Fold foil to seal.
Before last end is sealed, add 1/4 cup water.
Place on barbecue and cook for 45 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Bring cherry pie filling, water and sugar to a boil and pour over jello.
Add Coke plus a can full of water.
Let thicken slightly.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Pour into serving bowl. Refrigerate until set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rich banana pudding
directions: Line bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch dish with vanilla wafers.
Cover wafers completely with sliced bananas.
Overlap them a bit.
Prepare pudding according to package directions, using 3 cups milk.
Add sweetened condensed milk and fold in whipped topping.
Pour over bananas; chill and serve.
Serves 12 to 15, possibly more because it is very rich.
Keeps well overnight.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add margarine and shortening; use a pastry blender to cut shortening and margarine into flour mixture. Add ice water and mix well.
Roll out.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: marshmallow roll
directions: In a medium sized mixing bowl, blend together condensed milk and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cream.
Shape into rolls about 3 inches thick and 6 inches long.
Wrap and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Cut roll into 10 equal slices. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: berks county, potato filling
directions: Thoroughly mix mashed potatoes and eggs with a fork.
Add milk and set aside.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes and brown with onion in the butter.
Stir onion and bread into potato mixture and add seasonings.
Turn into a greased casserole and bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for 1 hour.
Serve as a vegetable.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased tube pan for 50 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, jello and water in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; add orange juice.
Chill until thickened.
Beat cream, Equal and vanilla until stiff.
Fold into chilled pudding mixture. Add sliced strawberries, mixing carefully with spoon.
Pour into pie shell and chill 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: hot and spicy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; add all ingredients with the water.
Simmer for 40 minutes.

title: spanish rice-a-roni
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and rice-vermicelli mix (from box) until vermicelli is golden brown.
Slowly stir in 2 cups water, special seasonings (from box) and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat to low.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: hello dollies
directions: In an 8 x 11 baking pan, make layers of the ingredients in the order above.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: 7- up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13 x 12 pan at 350° until brown, 30-35 minutes.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Brown onion in shortening.
Add seasonings and chicken.
Brown 10 minutes.
Add water and tomatoes.
Cover and let simmer slowly until tender.
Remove chicken, add sour cream to drippings in pan and mix well.
Add dumplings.
Arrange chicken on top.
Heat through and serve.

title: sweet delight
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix cake mix, butter and eggs together and press it into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: french bread
directions: Mix well, then rest for 10 minutes.
Knead for 10 minutes more, working flour in well.
Grease well.
Let rise until double. Punch down and knead for 30 seconds longer, letting it rise again.
Divide dough in half.
Brush on water, then coarse salt. Slash top with razor blade or sharp knife.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes with pan with water on bottom rack.

title: hurry curry fruit
directions: Combine all fruits in lightly oiled 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add sugar and curry powder to butter.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.
It may be made a day ahead and reheated just before serving.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut tops off pepper about 3/4-inch; save.
Remove seeds. Parboil 5 to 8 minutes.
Brown meat in fat; add onion and brown slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Should be stiff enough to hold shape of spoon.
Stuff peppers.
Replace tops and put into baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: meat-za-pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients and pat out in 9-inch pie plate on bottom and sides.
Spread catsup over meat mixture and arrange mushrooms on top.
Sprinkle cheese over this.
Two tablespoons Parmesan cheese may be sprinkled over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: mini cheddar cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into bite size balls and roll in finely chopped pecans.
Yield: 50 servings.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into frying pieces.
Add salt and pepper to chicken.
Set aside for 15 minutes.
Mix cream, water and eggs. Beat.
Pour cream mixture over chicken and allow to soak for 1 hour.
Add paprika to flour and then roll chicken in flour.
Melt bacon fat, shortening and butter in skillet.
Drop chicken in hot grease and fry on medium heat until golden brown.

title: butter balls
directions: Blend all ingredients. Roll into 1 to 1 1/2 inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool then roll in powdered sugar again.

title: halupkies(cabbage rolls)
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Cut core out of head of cabbage.
Scald head of cabbage and remove leaves.
Cut thick seam off cabbage leaves.
Split large leaves in half.
Put 1 tablespoon of filling in each cabbage leaf.
Roll and place in pan with seam down.
Blend 1 large can of tomatoes; add 1 tablespoon sugar, 1 tablespoon wine vinegar and remaining half of puree or sauce.
Pour over cabbage rolls; add enough tomatoes or water to cover rolls.
Cut up unused cabbage and place in pan. Bake at 325°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk and cocoa gradually at same time.
Cook and stir until thick; cook 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks; stir a little of chocolate mixture into them, then stir them into cooked mixture.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring well.
Add butter and vanilla.
Let cool to room temperature.
Pour into baked shell.
Cover with meringue and bake until brown.

title: chicken with sour cream
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Brown chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup bouillon (increase as needed).
Cook over low heat until chicken is tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Take out chicken; put on plate.
Add 1 tablespoon flour to sour cream; blend.
Add sour cream mixture to hot liquid.
Do not let boil; let warm.
Spoon over chicken for a gravy.

title: famous buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift together flour, sugar and soda. With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut shortening into flour mixture until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk.
Knead dough on floured board or cloth 10 times or until smooth.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut into 2 1/2-inch rounds with floured biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits, touching, on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Brush with melted butter immediately after removing from oven.
Makes 8 to 10 biscuits.

title: easy as pie cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries or fruit of choice.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Place prunes and apricots in 12 x 8 x 4-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over dried fruit.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
This is delicious for breakfast, lunch
or dinner.
Serves 12.

title: rolled mexican style flank steak
directions: Open steak like a book and flatten slightly.
Spread steak with 1/4 cup steak sauce.
Layer tomato, chilies and cheese.
Roll up steak from short edge; secure with toothpicks.
Place seam side down on 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with remaining steak sauce. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and chopped nuts.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring often.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Add dry ingredients to apples, then add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Pour batter into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Needs no icing.

title: cottage pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Drain off any fat; add bouillon cubes and water.
Mix well and cook 10 minutes. Meanwhile, cook and mash potatoes, season with butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Put the meat mixture in a greased baking dish. Spread the potatoes on top and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Then place under broiler for a few minutes to brown the top.

title: a 3-bean bake
directions: Brown the beef, bacon and onions; drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Stir margarine into spaghetti while it is hot. Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti into a crust in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of spaghetti crust.
Cook ground chuck, onions and green pepper until vegetables are tender and meat is brown.
Drain off excess fat. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt; simmer. Turn meat mixture into spaghetti crust.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
(May use Prego or Ragu spaghetti sauce instead of making this sauce.)

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: crusty beef cheese noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Combine the hamburger, Ragu and salt to sauteed mixture.
Cook 1/2 hour.
In casserole dish, put 1/2 noodles, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 grated cheese.
Sprinkle with Season-All spice.
Repeat with other half of mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash squash.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add 2 eggs (beaten), cracker crumbs, Velveeta cheese, mustard, salt and pepper and enough milk to make thin.
Dab top with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes (uncovered) or until light brown on top.
Serve hot.

title: tuna turnover delights
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a small bowl, mix together tuna, cheese, mayonnaise and lemon pepper seasoning. Prepare crescent rolls by rolling them into approximately 4 (5-inch) circles. Spoon tuna mixture onto crescent rolls. Fold crescent rolls together over tuna mixture. In another small bowl, melt butter and prepare crackers in a shallow dish. Dip turnovers in butter and then roll them in cracker crumbs. Place on an ungreased baking dish and bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until crescent rolls are golden brown.

title: squash fritters
directions: Blend well.
Melt 2 to 4 tablespoons margarine in skillet on medium heat.
Drop battered squash by spoonful into hot oil.
Fry on each side until done.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: bean and sausage chowder
directions: Melt butter in large kettle.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in flour and seasonings until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in beans and sausage.
Cover and simmer until lima beans are tender, 10 minutes or longer.
(For quicker cooking of limas, place in microwave and zap for 5 minutes or more before adding to pot.)
Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted.
Return to heat to finish melting cheese if necessary.
Do not boil.
Makes 8 cups.

title: microwave sweet and sour pork
directions: Place fork and teriyaki sauce in a deep 2-quart heat resistant, non-metallic casserole dish and marinate overnight. Remove meat from teriyaki sauce, reserving any remaining sauce. Brown meat in skillet on a conventional surface unit.

title: beef and cheese crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large frypan, brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain fat. Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, beans, garlic salt and salt.
Simmer while preparing crust.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Put milk, sugar, margarine and eggs in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add coconut, vanilla and nuts after mixture is thick.
Frosting is enough for a 2 layer cake.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni by pkg. directions and drain; rinse and drain well.
In a very large bowl, mix all other ingredients with macaroni and stir until blended.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring butter, brown sugar, salt and syrup to a boil; cook about 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from stove.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Stir until foamy.
Pour over popped corn.
Put in greased pan and bake at 250° for one hour in oven, then remove, then break up while hot.

title: chile verde con carne
directions: Flour and brown the meat in the grease in a Dutch oven.
In a separate pan, saute onion.
Add this to the meat, together with the tomatoes, chiles, salt, oregano, cumin and beef broth.
Cook, covered, at 325° for about 4 hours.
If consistency is too thin, thicken with flour, stirred in water.
Serve with warm flour tortillas.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Saut meat. Cut into chunks with wooden spoon and cook for 10 minutes. Add onions and garlic, stirring frequently until meat is browned and vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes. Add sugar, salt, basil, oregano and crushed red pepper. Mix well. Add tomatoes, tomato paste and tomato puree. Mash tomatoes with wooden spoon. Bring to boiling; reduce heat, simmer, covered, stirring occasionally until thickened for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Makes 3 quarts. One quart is enough for 1/2 pound of spaghetti.

title: red devil food cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Mix soda into buttermilk. Add eggs and buttermilk mixture.
In small saucepan, heat Crisco with water and add.
Stir until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until tested done.

title: bacon spaghetti
directions: Cut bacon into pieces and fry until crisp.
Put tomatoes and Ro-Tel in blender and blend 1 minute.
Pour into saucepan and heat thoroughly.
Saute chopped onion and garlic.
Add to tomatoes. Cook spaghetti and add to tomatoes. Stir in bacon and serve.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake in a 300° oven for 40 minutes.
Makes 12 pies.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, soda, salt and cloves.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and cooking oil until thoroughly combined.
Spread batter into ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Cut into bars.
Makes 48.

title: saturday chicken
directions: Salt and garlic salt chicken a bit, then paprika it thoroughly.
Spread it out in one layer in a shallow baking pan. Dilute the soup with the cream; pour it over the chicken and sprinkle the chopped parsley prettily on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for
1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Heat soups and milk, stirring occasionally.
Stir in shrimp; heat through.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cook pineapple, cornstarch and 1/4 cup sugar until it starts to thicken.
Put in pie shell.
Mix the other ingredients with mixer; pour over first layer.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: soft cut-out cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar. Add egg and milk. Beat well. Add and blend the remaining ingredients. Place teaspoons of batter on cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees for 5-8 minutes.

title: rice zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini, squash and onion in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, basil and salt.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 of rice and 1/2 of tomato-vegetable mixture.
Repeat.
Spread beans on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: yellow rice and chicken(columbia restaurant)
directions: *For each cup of rice, use 2 cups of broth.
To make broth, boil bony pieces of chicken or use chicken flavored bouillon cubes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil, peel and mash sweet potatoes.
Add butter, salt, egg, pineapple and pecans; whip lightly.
Mix in spices and molasses. Roll into balls and press marshmallow into the center of each ball with thumb.
Roll in hot honey and then in flaked coconut (or chopped nuts, or serve plain).
Pineapple could also be left out and nuts on inside could also be left out.

title: jicama and orange salad
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together the lime juice, salt, chili powder and cayenne.
Add the jicama, which is peeled and cut into 1/3-inch strips.
Arrange orange sections decoratively around the edge of a platter and use a slotted spoon to mound the jicama in the center.
Drizzle the dressing remaining in the bowl over the oranges and sprinkle the green onions over the salad.

title: creole lima beans
directions: Heat tomatoes to boiling in 1-quart saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, separating green beans with fork.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until beans are tender (5 minutes). Serves 5.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix margarine, chocolate chips, milk and powdered sugar. Bring to a boil over low heat.
Boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: turkey and spinach quiche
directions: Place pie crust in a 1 1/2-inch deep quiche dish.
Pierce pastry shell thoroughly with fork.
Bake in 375° oven 10 minutes; remove.
Set oven at 350°.
In large bowl, toss together turkey, cheese, spinach and onion; spoon into pastry shell.
In small bowl, stir together eggs, mayonnaise, milk, basil and pepper until smooth.
Pour over turkey mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.
This is perfect for using up the last few pieces of leftover turkey.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: granola
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients thoroughly.
Then, mix the water, vanilla and oil and pour over first mixture and blend.
Spread on cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir every 30 to 45 minutes.

title: escalloped corn
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, layer corn, salt, pepper, crumbs and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Repeat.
Beat egg, sugar and milk together.
Pour over corn.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cover for 1/2 hour, then uncover and top with paprika.

title: mama white fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Cook at least a week or so in advance; seal good and refrigerate.

title: saucy manicotti
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Add tomato sauce and next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Place the ingredients in layers in a 2 quart baking dish with a tight fitting lid. First the rice followed by the corn. Salt & pepper and then pour over 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2

can water. The next is the onion and green pepper. Put the ground beef on next. Sprinkle with salt & pepper and then add other can of tomato sauce and 1/4 can of water. Cover the meat with the bacon. Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350 degrees. Uncover and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: soy cocktail sauce
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and chill.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: ole buttermilk pie
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and salt into a nice mountain and set aside.
Beat the eggs into lemony mish-mash and blend this into buttermilk.
Pour this into the dry ingredients.
Mix well and add flavoring.
Pour equal amounts into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 375° until it looks thick, about 30 minutes.

title: cotillion punch
directions: Boil the sugar with water and add all the juices.
Cool and put in 3 (1/2 gallon) milk cartons and freeze.
When ready to use, partially thaw and add 2 large bottles of 7-Up per carton.
Makes approximately 80 (6 ounce) servings.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa.
Pour in milk and place butter on top. Microwave for 2 minutes and stir.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; mix in remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
May top with sugar, butter and cinnamon, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaves.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add some bread crumbs to the top and bake 10 more minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together well all ingredients, except cheese. Pour into large casserole, well greased. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven. Put cheese on 10 minutes before serving.

title: classic baked pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350`.
Prepare pasta as package directs.
In a large bowl, combine pasta, ground beef, spaghetti sauce and 2 cups cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish; cover.
Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Uncover; top with remaining 2 cups cheese and parsley.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: blender eggnog
directions: Stir or beat in blender all of the ingredients.
May add nutmeg, if desired.

title: wiener bean pot
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
Blend flour, 1/4 cup 10x sugar and butter with hands. Form into a ball.
Spread on a 13-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: reeses chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: nibbles
directions: Combine all cereals, pretzels and nuts.
In saucepan, melt margarine.
Combine with Worcestershire sauce and seasonings. Toss with the cereals and add peanuts.
Place in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together first five ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: raisin oatmeal ribbons
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and oats.
Cut in margarine to form crumbs.
Pat 1/2 mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling over base.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top; pat gently.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: party rye
directions: In a skillet, brown meat and sausage; drain.
Add cheese and cook until melted.
Add Worcestershire sauce and oregano and mix. Spread on bread and place on cookie sheet.
Freeze until solid. (Once frozen, can be stacked in freezer for future use.)
Bake frozen on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs and milk; stir in crumbs, onions, parsley, salt, sage and pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Pat into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Spoon off fat.
Combine catsup, sugar and mustard; spread over meat.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In a large, heavy frypan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add carrots, raisins, broth and sugar.

Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until carrots are crisp-tender, about 10 minutes. Uncover and boil over high heat until liquid has evaporated, shaking pan often and gently lifting and turning carrots.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease (or spray) a 1-quart souffle dish.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, broccoli and flour. Add butter, 1/2 cup cheese, salt, pepper and onion. Transfer to souffle dish and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until set.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Put pieces in pan.
Follow directions on pudding box and fix pudding.
Then add Cool Whip and sour cream to pudding.
Pour over cake.
Break candy bars into crushed up pieces.
Sprinkle over cake.
You can use different kinds of candy bars.
Serves 20.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour, at once.
Combine flour and water, alternating, until used up.
Pour into 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: play clay
directions: Mix well.
Roll out and cut into shapes with cookie cutters. Let dry, then paint them.

title: poor shepherd's pie
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Put mixed vegetables, peas and corn in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put hamburger on bottom of pan, then put the vegetables over hamburger.
Make instant potatoes; place on top of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are brown.

title: rosy rhubarb betty
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients, except cinnamon and coconut.
Toss lightly to mix.
Spread mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and cinnamon on top.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: stuffing andrew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread cubes in a large bowl. Melt butter in saute pan.
Add onion, celery and seasonings. Saute on medium-high heat until onions are soft and clear; add to bread cubes.
Next, add the chicken broth.
Mix thoroughly.
Place mixture in an oven pan and spread evenly.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes or until the top is golden brown.
Transfer to a serving dish and enjoy!
Serves 5 to 6.

title: texas chicken and dumplings
directions: In large pot, half cover chicken with water.
Add onion, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cover; simmer until chicken is done.
Remove chicken; skin and debone.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Roll out and bake like regular biscuits.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together in large saucepan and heat until it simmers. Layer with corn or flour tortillas in a casserole dish.
Top with a little of the grated cheese.
Put in 350° oven about 30 minutes until hot and cheese is melted.
Serve with tostadas and green salad.

title: naked apple pie
directions: Beat egg in medium sized bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and spread in a greased 9-inch pie plate; bake 30 minutes at 350°. It's a pie without a crust and very good eating.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies (food processor works well); set aside. Cream together margarine and cream cheese with powdered sugar. Mix milk with pudding mixes.
Combine the 2 mixtures; fold in Cool Whip.

title: kerk's grandma's apple cake
directions: For cake:
Mix sugar and shortening, then rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch round cake pan.
Press apple slices into batter.
Mix all topping ingredients together until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apple slices.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake and fudge frosting
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
In a medium bowl, sift flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Separately, combine milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, beating well.

title: grasshopper cocktail
directions: Mix in blender for a very short time (couple of seconds). Serve immediately.
Also good as an after dinner drink.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and orange through a grinder or in a food processor. Add sugar and nuts, blending gently with a spoon. Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Wash the artichokes well and boil in covered pot 45 minutes to 1 hour.
When ready, peel them until you can see the center. Remove the "chokes" with a spoon and discard.
Cut the artichoke heart and other vegetables into bite size pieces.
Combine and toss with vinegar and oil.

title: rye rounds
directions: Twenty-four hours in advance, spread a good amount of cream cheese on rye bread slices.
Place a thin slice of cucumber on top of cheese.
Sprinkle dry dressing over top of cucumber.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, oil, water, salt and spices.
Add pumpkin (1 pound can), soda and flour.
Add pecans now if you desire.
Grease 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pina colada cake
directions: While cake is hot, mix pina colada and Eagle Brand milk together and punch holes in cake with toothpick; pour over cake very slowly so it can soak in.
Use only half on this or it will be too soggy.
Cool in refrigerator, then ice with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in baking dish. Add the peaches. Combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over peaches. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add chips and grated Hershey bar.
Add chopped nuts.
Make golf-sized balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet or drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 6 minutes.

title: 24 hour pickles
directions: Bring water, vinegar, sugar and salt to a rapid boil.
Cool completely.
Liquid should be enough to fill 3 jars (depending on size).
Wash jars and lids.
Cut cucumbers to desired size and pack into jars.
Add 2 cloves garlic and dill (fresh or dried) or dill seed per jar.
Pour completely cooled liquid into jars. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Must be kept in refrigerator.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: citrus punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Add orange juice concentrate, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Let cool.
Pour into Cool Whip bowls, approximately 5 or 6.
Freeze.

title: chopped salad
directions: Chop all vegetables very fine.
In a large bowl, mix chopped vegetables with wheat germ.
Add tomato sauce, lemon juice, olive oil and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Combine all in saucepan; heat until cheese is melted.
Stir often.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix in order given using enough milk. This will thicken as it cooks. Crush potato chips and sprinkle over top of mixture. Bake 1 hour, uncovered at 325°.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows in pan.
Cook until marshmallows melt.
Add jello; dissolve.
Add cream cheese to hot mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Cool.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Chill until set.

title: a loving heart
directions: Practice daily.
Get the full benefit of what God has given all.

title: sugar rolled cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough to desired thickness on floured cloth covered board.
Cut into shapes.
Bake until light brown, 7 to 8 minutes.
Frost.

title: chicken and rice casserole(grandma's recipe)
directions: Mix rice and soups together.
Place mixture in the bottom of a greased baking dish.
Clean and arrange chicken pieces on top of rice.
Then season chicken pieces with garlic salt or powder and Lawry's seasoning salt.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours or a 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6 depending on the amount of chicken used.

title: stew for two
directions: Trim all fat off meat and cut in small pieces.
Brown and simmer in 1 cup water for 1/2 hour.
Put all vegetables in, cover with water and simmer 1 hour.
Add tomato sauce; cook a minute. Thicken gravy and put over potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: mom's cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Peel cucumbers with potato peeler; slice very thin.
Place on paper towel to dry for about 1 hour.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate and serve chilled.
You can also use zucchini in place of cucumbers.

title: sweet and sour shrimp
directions: Preheat frypan.
Melt butter in frypan.
Saute shrimp 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple (with juice), ginger, green pepper, vinegar, sugar and soy sauce.
Blend well. Cover.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Spoon out a little liquid and mix with cornstarch.
Pour into shrimp mixture and cook until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Serve over rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: sue's chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix
all
together,
except for chips.	Beat for 2 minutes. Fold in chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until tender.
Add salt, pepper, beef base and chili powder.
Add all canned ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: wassail
directions: Try this twist on grilled cheese sandwiches.
Rather than buttering the outside of the bread, use mayonnaise (not salad dressing).
It gives the sandwich a different texture and makes it less greasy.

title: lazy lady egg pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and mix.
Pour in a pie plate.
Bake at 300° until center is set.

title: southern corn custard
directions: Combine the beaten eggs, corn, melted butter and milk.
Stir well.
Add the seasonings and sugar.
Pour into a well buttered casserole; dot with butter and bake in a very slow oven (250°) for about 40 minutes or until custard has set.

title: black bean soup guatemala
directions: To a cup of condensed black bean soup, add 1 can water, 1 teaspoon meat extract, 1 teaspoon Kitchen Bouquet and 1 teaspoon onion juice.
Simmer for a few minutes and just before taking off fire, add 2 to 4 tablespoons sherry or wine.
Do not boil after adding wine.
Serve with sliced egg, lemon or lime slices, and pass the Tabasco or hot sauce around the table.

title: marinated fresh vegetable salad
directions: Slice and layer ingredients in order given.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add 1/2 dry sifted ingredients to creamed mixture. Add mincemeat and water and stir until blended. Add nuts and remaining flour. Mix well. Bake at 350° on a greased baking sheet for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tres' 7 layer dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomato paste and water and let simmer 10 minutes.
Put vegetables in 2-quart greased casserole.
Pour hamburger mixture over vegetables.
Mix together.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Check carrots to make sure it's finished.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Take oblong pan, melt butter in it.
Sprinkle brown sugar on melted butter.
Place 12 pineapple rings on bottom of buttered pan and put cherries inside rings of pineapple.
Mix cake mix and pour over pineapple and cherries.
Bake 35 minutes or until brown.
Turn upside-down on cake box.

title: georgia's cabbage soup
directions: Mix together in large pot and simmer on low heat until tender or about an hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and serve with crispy crackers or raw veggies.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for a couple of minutes.
Pour chocolate candy, chocolate bits, marshmallow cream and nuts into sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and allow to cool.
When completely cool, cut into squares.

title: easy butterscotch pudding
directions: Bring milk and butter to a boil.
Beat rest of ingredients together and stir into hot milk.
Continue stirring until pudding is thick.
Beat again before serving.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain well.
Add chili powder and cook for a minute.
Then add salt, garlic juice and tomato sauce. Simmer, covered, over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add 2 cups water.
Cook in a heavy pan over low heat for at least 2 hours. The longer it cooks the better.
Add beans, undrained, in the last 30 minutes of cooking.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie shell and bake for 10 minutes.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, syrup and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Wash lettuce and drain well.
Tear into bite-sized pieces and place in plastic bags.
Refrigerate.

title: dill pickles
directions: Make a brine of vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to a boil. Sprinkle a layer of minced garlic in a hot jar.
Add 1 or 2 sprigs of fresh dill.
Fill with cucumbers and add another sprig of fresh dill.
Pour in brine.
Seal.

title: my mother's pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Makes 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: special party punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice into punch bowl.
Add ice cream and sherbet by small scoopfuls.
Add ginger ale and stir slightly. Serve punch immediately.
Makes 7 1/2 quarts.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef in frypan.
Drain oil off meat.
Add to vegetables and water.
Cook on medium heat about 6 hours or crock-pot all day.

title: fudge
directions: In a large stainless steel pot, melt margarine and blend in milk.
Add sugar while stirring. Bring to a boil and boil 8 minutes slowly, stirring all the time. Don't let it stick or burn, if at all possible.
Take off stove and add flavoring and chocolate chips. Beat until melted.
Beat in marshmallow cream and nuts.
Mix real good.
Pour in a large buttered pan.
Put in the refrigerator.
When cold, cut in squares.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Mix soups, chiles and olives.
Alternate layers of torn tortillas, sauce, topping bottom layer with the Jack cheese and the top layer with the Cheddar cheese.
Let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all together in blender.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat until light and fluffy. Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, except walnuts.
Mix together and add to first mixture.
Add walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sugar spice pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Stir in sugar, salt, and cinnamon.
Add pecans and stir well until pecans are completely coated.
Spread onto large ungreased cookie sheet with an edge.
Bake at 200 degrees for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, cool, and store in an airtight container.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, squash, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add nuts and raisins or dates and bake in 2 large loaf pans about 1 hour at 350°, or bake in 4 (1 pound size) loaf pans until done.
Real good for freezing.

title: grilled london broil
directions: Pierce steak with fork.
To marinate, place meat in a plastic bag; set in a deep bowl.
In a skillet over medium heat, cook onion in oil until tender; remove from heat.
Add catsup, vinegar, relish, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and pepper to skillet; mix well and cool.
Pour marinade over meat; close bag.
Marinate in refrigerator for 6 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove meat, reserving the marinade.
Transfer meat to grill.
Brush with marinade.
Grill for 10 to 12 minutes.
Turn and continue to grill 10 to 12 minutes more to desired doneness.
(Or may bake at 250° to desired doneness.)
To serve, thinly slice across grain. Makes 6 servings.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Bake in a 13 x 9 pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sweet and hot, delicious with "Sam's" chili.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Spread rice in bottom of rectangular baking dish.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of seasoning from envelope of onion soup mix and sprinkle remaining seasonings and bits over rice.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid and distribute mushrooms and pimiento over rice.
Add hot water to mushroom liquid to a total of 3 cups.
Pour over rice.
Arrange browned chops on top of rice mixture and sprinkle remaining seasoning.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil; let stand 10 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, hot water and bouillon.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat. Stir in sour cream.
In medium bowl combine 2 cups of the sauce mixture with chicken, 1 cup of the cheese, chilies and cumin. Place chicken mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up, folding in sides.
Arrange in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender, then pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: disappearing marshmallow brownies
