directions: Mix the butterscotch pieces and margarine; melt over medium heat.
Remove; let cool.

Add the flour, baking powder, vanilla, brown sugar, salt and eggs to the mixture in saucepan; mix well. Fold the marshmallows, chocolate pieces and nuts into other mixture, then spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix with other ingredients. Cover with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion; saute until onion is brown. Drain grease.
Add small amount water.
Add beans, using liquid. Add taco seasoning; simmer.
Add more water if necessary.
In large mixing bowl, break up lettuce in small pieces.
Add 2/3 of chips, cut up tomato and cheese.
After salad mix is prepared, pour hot mixture over salad; lightly toss.
Serve with remaining chips.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Use a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer hash browns, sausage, cheese, pepper and onions.
Combine eggs and milk, beating well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over layers. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Can be refrigerated or frozen. Makes 12 servings.

title: frypan pizza
directions: Liberally grease a cool, electric skillet.
Mix biscuit mix and milk; spread evenly in skillet.
Spread pizza sauce evenly over dough; layer ground beef, onion and any other toppings of your choice over pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover pan, but leave vent open.
Set control at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes until crust is brown on bottom and cheese is melted.
Makes 10 to 11-inch pizza.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and eggs and bring to boil around edges. Add lemon juice.
Cool in pan of cold water.
Whip Carnation milk; add mixture and whip again.

title: pheasant for 1
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over pheasant.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Baste with sauce.

title: won ton chicken salad
directions: Tear green spinach or leaf lettuce or use a variety of greens. Add the diced meat, mandarin oranges, red and green pepper strips, onions and won ton strips (1/4 to 1/2-inch wide) or fried rice sticks.
Pour dressing over salad and toss.
May sprinkle toasted sesame seed on top.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin and Jell-O in boiling water; stir until mixed well.
Pour in rectangular pan and refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and put in crock-pot.
Empty all other ingredients.
Stir and mix all together and cook for 3 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: sunny fruit mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add cold water. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruit and celery. Pour into mold. Chill until firm. At serving time, unmold on crisp lettuce. Serves 6.

title: maine fish chowder
directions: Slowly "try out" salt pork or bacon until crisp.
Pour off most of fat.
Add onions and cook slowly until yellow.
Add potatoes and water to nearly cover.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Place cut up fish on top.
Season.
Add more water, if necessary, and bring to simmer.
Cover, cook on lowered heat until potatoes are done (10 minutes).
Meanwhile, in top of double boiler, heat milk and butter.
Add to cooked fish mixture.
Cool and refrigerate 8 hours before reheating to serve.
Serves 6.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add apples and stir.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Drizzle with milk; dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: This recipe is handed down from one generation to the next. It dates back 108 years.

title: italian stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet.
Add garlic; cook 1 minute.
Add all remaining ingredients, except 2 tablespoons oil; mix well.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Melt butter and oil in a flat pan in a 375° oven.
Set aside. Combine flour and seasonings in a paper bag.
Roll the meat through the melted oil and butter.
Put chicken in bag (3 pieces at a time).
Shake well.
Place coated pieces on a piece of waxed paper.
Coat remaining chicken.
Place chicken in the oiled pan. Bake for 45 minutes at 375° (skin side down).
Using a spatula, turn the chicken pieces and bake 5 or 10 minutes longer.
Use pan drippings for gravy.

title: potato pancakes(reibekuchen)
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Put eggs in a blender.
Add potato slices, onion and salt.
Blend a few seconds; add flour.
Blend well.
Heat oil in a frying pan until hot.
Pour potato mixture into pan, about 1/4 cup for each pancake.
Fry until brown on each side.
Eat with applesauce or sour cream.

title: no fat mocha cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of a 9-inch diameter cake pan with 1
inch high sides with waxed paper.
Spray pan and paper with
vegetable
oil spray (or oil pan and paper lightly). Dust pan with flour; tap out excess.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar.
Sprinkle 3/4 of crumbs in bottom of pie shell.
Pour in cooked vanilla pudding.
When cold, spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except oatmeal in hot water and stir until all blended, then add oatmeal until consistency required to press into cookies.
Place in refrigerator until served.
You may freeze and use as needed.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large microwavable bowl on High 2 or 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in vanilla, walnuts and marshmallows.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Cut into squares.

title: dell's sugar cookies
directions: Bake in 425 degree oven.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Cut trimmed sirloin into 1 inch cubes.
Combine: white wine, olive oil, red wine vinegar, mustard, garlic, black pepper, and sugar.
Put beef in a plastic bag; add marinade.
Close bag, marinate for 30 minutes.
Pour off marinade, reserve.
Thread 4 to 5 beef cubes onto each of 4 skewers.
Broil or grill 10 to 13 minutes, turn and brush with reserved marinade occasionally.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare the cake according to directions.
Making 2 layers, bake, cool and split both layers horizontally.
Blend together sugar, sour cream, and coconut.
Chill.
Spread all but 1 cup of the sour cream mixture between layers.
Blend the remaining cup of the mixture with the cool whip or whipped cream and spread on the top and sides of the cake.
Seal in an air tight container and refrigerate.
Cake is better after three or four days.

title: hot tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Use 2 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup boiling water.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; saute onions and celery.
Add to hamburger all ingredients.
Mix together well.
Simmer 3 hours.

title: wild rice mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in a large soup kettle over medium heat.
Peel the mushrooms and cut off the woody part of the stems.
(Washed mushrooms don't saute as well as peeled mushrooms.)
Add basil, oregano, thyme and grated onion with juice.
Cover the kettle; let the mushrooms sweat over medium-low heat for about 10 minutes or until they are fairly soft and limp.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Add Bisquick and roll into small balls or roll and cut as biscuit.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 105 balls.

title: new orleans chili
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add water to desired thickness. Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix the ingredients until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
If using a glass pan, bake at 325°.

title: no cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt margarine in large skillet or pot on top of stove. Stir in package of stuffing; make sure stuffing has absorbed all of the butter. Pour stuffing on top of broccoli mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, checking frequently the last 10 minutes to be sure stuffing does not get too brown.

title: lima beans and pears
directions: Place all ingredients in a heavy casserole dish; cover and bake 12 hours at 200°.

title: chili vesuvius
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Saute garlic and vegetables in olive oil.
Combine drained hamburger with tomatoes, beans and salsa.

Add spices and herbs, including salt and pepper to taste. Add sauteed vegetables; do not drain olive oil, add to mixture. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 to 2 hours to suit. Serves 10+ hearty appetites.
Serve with Italian bread.

title: baked brie
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in heavy medium skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic and saute until onion is golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Place Brie and cream cheese in large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on Medium just until melted, about 2 minutes.
Whisk in onion mixture, sour cream, fresh lemon juice, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cut off top of bread loaf.
Scoop out center of loaf, leaving a 3/4-inch thick shell of bread.
Spoon cheese mixture into loaf.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead; refrigerate. Let stand 2 hours at room temperature before continuing.)
Wrap in foil.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake loaf until filling bubbles, about 1 hour.
Unwrap and place on platter.
Remove bread lid. Sprinkle cheese mixture with paprika.
Serve with crudites or crackers.

title: sour cream meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, 1/2 cup sour cream, milk, bread crumbs, onions, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and hamburger.
Put into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole(made with hamburger)
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper.
Cook noodles.
Melt velveeta and rotel and mix in microwave.
Drain noodles.
Combine cheese soup, mushroom soup, ground meat and cheese/rotel mixture. Mix well.
Put in baking dish, cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: pink hawaiian salad
directions: In a heavy saucepan melt gelatin, pineapple and marshmallows, stirring constantly.
Refrigerate until thick like jam.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese and Dream Whip mixture and fold into gelatin.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: people chow
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips until smooth.
Add peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Add Crispix to mixture, rolling and folding slowly so the cereal doesn't break.
Put 2 cups powdered sugar into grocery bag.
Add mixture to powdered sugar.
Shake until cereal is well coated.
Let cool on wax paper.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Cook all ingredients to 290 degrees on stove top.
Cut off stove.
Add 2 tsp. soda.
Stir well, pour on greased dish.
Break apart when cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion (cut up).
Cook noodles as directed on box.
Drain hamburger and cool noodles.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan add sauce, oregano, garlic salt and hamburger meat.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
In a large casserole layer noodles, sharp cheese, regular Kraft cheese, Mozzarella, another layer of noodles and 1/2 of the sauce.
Repeat procedure with noodles, cheeses and sauce.
Cook for 40 minutes.

title: chicken piquant
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Combine rest of ingredients to make marinade.
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze.
Return to room temperature.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Or, to grill, remove from marinade and, wearing oven mitts, carefully brush marinade on chicken as it cooks.
Yields 8 servings.
Each contains 5 g fat and 141 calories.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in ovenproof dish (10-inch quiche dish is ideal).
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes until golden and bubbling.
Serve with thinly sliced French bread.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Pan Preparations:
Grease a 10 x 15 1/2-inch cookie sheet with shortening.
Cut wax paper to fit the bottom of the cookie sheet. Place the fitted wax paper in the bottom of the cookie sheet, then grease the top of the wax paper, too, spreading evenly.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain all fruits.
Mix together and put into 2 to 3 graham cracker crusts.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: two-tone fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients (sugars, milk and butter).
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly over moderate heat.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; mix until smooth. To 2 cups of mixture, add butterscotch (peanut butter) pieces and 1/2 cup of the walnuts; blend well.
Pour evenly into greased 9-inch square pan.
To remaining hot mixture, add chocolate pieces and 1/2 cup walnuts; blend well.
Pour over butterscotch (peanut butter) mixture.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Microwave chocolate chips 2 1/2 minutes on medium setting. Stir twice.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes more, until soft, stirring until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Place round tablespoonfuls on cookie sheet or wax paper.
Place in refrigerator 20 minutes.

title: squirrel mulligan
directions: Boil squirrels until tender; debone.
Add tomatoes, onions and seasonings and cook until vegetables are done.
Cook rice separately.
Fry bacon crisp and save drippings.
Add corn, hominy and rice and bring to a boil.
Stir in chopped bacon, bacon drippings and sliced eggs.
The longer it cooks the better it tastes.
Serve hot with cornbread.

title: fast and easy barbecue(kids recipe #1)
directions: Tear ham into pieces and mix with sauce in small skillet. Saute 2 minutes or until hot all through.
Serve on bun or toasted bread.

title: mini meat loaf(serves 6)
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and 1/8 teaspoon each pepper, sage and thyme.
Shape firmly into 6 mini meat loaves.
In skillet, brown loaves in shortening. Stir in remaining soup and seasonings and water.
Cook over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Stir in rice and coat well.
Add soup and water.
Cook (covered)
at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Layer water chestnuts, chicken, asparagus and almonds in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine next four ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon mixture over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and place in enough boiling salted water to cover. With a fork in one hand and a knife in the other, keep cutting off the leaves as they become wilted. Drain. Trim thick center vein of each cabbage leaf. Brown the onion in shortening. Add to meat, seasonings and rice; mix well. Place a tablespoon of filling on each cabbage leaf and roll, tucking in edges. Place in pot and cover 2/3 full with water; arrange sauerkraut on top; add tomato juice. Cover and cook slowly for about 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender. Serves 6 to 8 people. You can substitute green pepper for the cabbage or use both. For green peppers, cut off tops, scoup out center and fill peppers about 2/3 full with filling. Cook as directed for cabbage.

title: beef and vegetable dish
directions: Brown meat, onion
and	pepper	in
oil; add seasoning, tomatoes, corn and bouillon.
Bring
to
a boil; stir in rice. Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes and fluff with a fork.

title: swiss onion potato bake
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
In a large bowl, mix onion, potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned. Allow to cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Combine biscuit mix and water, stirring with a fork until blended.
Press mixture in bottom of a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.
Cook ground beef, green pepper and onion in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce; spoon over crust.
Combine sour cream, cheese and mayonnaise; spoon over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Cut into squares to serve.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 items together and pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: claire's chicken 'n' dressing casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and put half into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and add to cornbread in dish. Top with remaining cornbread mixture.
Beat the eggs and add milk to make 1 cup.
Pour over the top of the casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Right before baking, add the mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 10 minutes.

title: chicken blush
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for one hour or until done.
This is a great picnic item.

title: indian corn
directions: Chop pepper and onion; fry in skillet.
Brown ground beef in a large skillet.
Add green pepper, onion, sugar, salt, chili powder and tomatoes.
Cook until nearly done.
Add drained corn and red beans.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: grandma carol's welsh pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing until there are no lumps. Heat 8 to 10-inch crepe pan or skillet to medium heat.
Pour in enough batter so pancake will just barely fill pan (these will be as thin as crepes).
Turn pancake when lightly browned and cook on second side to light brown.
Remove pancake from skillet and repeat until you cook all the batter.
Place pancakes on plate and sprinkle with undiluted, straight lemon juice.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and roll pancake up.
Serve rolled.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake, 35 to 40 minutes, at 350° in a square or oblong baking dish.
Can also be baked in a Bundt pan for 55 to 60 minutes.
Check for doneness by inserting a toothpick in center of cake, if it comes out clean, it's done.
After about 5 minutes or so of cooking, turn cake over on plate.

title: gourmet chicken breast
directions: Line a pan or glass casserole with dried beef.
Wrap each piece of chicken with a strip of bacon and place in pan.
Top with mushroom or chicken soup mixed with sour cream.
Place in oven at 275° for 3 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach or apricot hot tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together; store in airtight container. When ready to use, mix 2 to 3 teaspoons of tea mix to 6 to 8 ounces of hot water.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Cut bread into cubes and place half in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cube the cream cheese and place on top of the bread.
Top with remaining bread.

title: dolly's pineapple drops
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Stir in undrained pineapple and nuts.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and frost, if desired.
Yields 4 dozen soft cookies.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage and chop medium fine.
Heat tomatoes, corned beef and salt in saucepan to boiling.
Add cabbage.
Cover.
Cook quickly until cabbage is tender.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix eggs and milk in medium bowl.
Dip chicken in egg mix, then bread chicken.
Heat oil in pan.
Cook chicken in oil over medium heat.
Drain on paper bag.
Put sauce on cookie sheet.
Put chicken on sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on chicken.
Put some sauce over chicken.
Place 1 slice of Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake in oven at 400° until Mozzarella cheese bubbles. Serve hot.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Mix in the peanut butter and oats.
Drop on wax paper.

title: marsha's sour cream drop cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix together sour cream and vanilla and add.
Mix together flour, baking soda and salt and add. Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon drops 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 9 minutes, until top springs up.

title: strawberry party punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool.
In large punch bowl, combine gelatin mixture, lemonade concentrate, orange juice concentrate and cold water.
Just before serving, gently stir in ginger ale.
Makes 28 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook pinto beans, smoked sausage, onion, bell pepper and ham hock until done.
Add red pepper, salt, pepper and tomato sauce. I also add a little chili powder to mine for taste.
Cook until all ingredients' flavor combine.
Serve over rice.

title: horseradish
directions: Put horseradish cubes in blender and blend until grated.
Mix all ingredients together and put into tightly covered jar.

title: getting the fat out(use this to make soups, gravies or seasoning for veggies)
directions: If you don't have time to prepare this broth to keep in the freezer, just buy canned broth and place the unopened can in the refrigerator.
Chill for 1 hour and skim off the fat when you open the can.

title: red cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1 cup juice.
Set cherries aside. Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon in a medium saucepan; stir mixture to remove lumps.
Stir cherry juice into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cherries, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and almond extract.
Stir in food coloring. Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Spray a baking dish with Pam and line chicken in dish in a single layer.
Combine oil, lemon juice, garlic powder and brush on chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° preheated oven for 35 minutes. Remove cover and brush again with lemon oil mixture.
Bake another 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
This recipe can be used on chicken breasts too.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Combine beans, onions, carrot and oleo in a large pot.
Cover with water.
Pepper to taste.
Cook until beans and vegetables are tender.
Add ham the last 20 minutes of cooking time.
Serve with corn bread or corn sticks.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix all ingredients; heat milk and butter. Add marshmallows, then mix well with other ingredients to form cake in a large pan or tube pan.
Put in refrigerator until it is set.

title: chinese style country ribs(for crock-pot, slow cooker)
directions: Combine soy sauce, marmalade, catsup and garlic.
Brush on both sides of ribs.
Place in slow cooking pot.
Pour remaining sauce over all.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
(I usually use beef ribs and on high about 3 to 4 hours until done.)

title: vanilla wafer icebox cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in order given.
Line bottom of a glass cake dish with layer of wafer crumbs.
Top this with layer of pineapple mixture.
Alternate layers of wafer crumbs and pineapple mixture, finishing with wafer crumbs on top.
Place in refrigerator 3 or 4 hours.
To serve, garnish with whipped cream and maraschino cherries.
Makes 6 servings.
(Any other crushed fruit may be used in place of pineapple.)

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and rum extract.
Sift flour with salt; add sour cream, save 2 tablespoons sour cream.
Blend baking soda into the saved sour cream and add to butter, stirring to blend.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: grandma's corn relish
directions: Combine vegetables (corn, cabbage, onions, green peppers, celery, red peppers) in a large pot or Dutch oven.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Ladle into hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Let stand 1 hour to blend flavors.
Yields 14 (12 oz.) jars.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix Ritz crackers and oleo.
Spread half in bottom of 9x13 casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream, & poppy seed.
Add chicken & rice.
Pour into casserole over crackers.
Top with remaining Ritz. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Cook egg noodles separately for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not salt; drain.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until soft and slightly brown.

In large kettle, bring chicken broth to boil. Add frozen broccoli, ham, parsley, garlic, onions and mushrooms. When mixture returns to a boil add cooked noodles and cubed cheese, reducing heat to a lower temperature.
When cheese is melted, add milk.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Into a bowl sift flour with other dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk, then yeast mixture.
Stir until all flour is dampened.
Knead on floured board for a minute or two.
Roll out to desired thickness (1/2 to 3/4 inch) and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook onions in butter until soft.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add onions to liquid.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Pour in earthenware bowls.
Place toast on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out over round or square pan (fit best you can).
Cover rolls with sausage, hash browns (uncooked), Cheddar cheese and vegetables of choice.
You can cover and refrigerate overnight before cooking.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over pizza.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked steak
directions: Wash steak and pat dry.
Place in baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle lemon juice over meat.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread over meat.
Dot with butter, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: super date nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: rosa marina salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well, reserving liquid. Refrigerate fruit.
Cook pasta until tender. Drain.
Make custard of fruit juices, salt sugar and flour.
Mix custard
and pasta and refrigerate overnight.
Combine fruits and whipped topping.
Add to pasta when ready to serve.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolk until a lemon color.
Beat egg whites.
Add egg yolk, sugar and flour.
Add hot water and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Add stiffly beaten egg whites last. Bake in a well-greased pan in 350° oven.

title: baked chicken with almond rice
directions: Brown chicken on all sides in butter in a large skillet.
In a separate pan, combine chicken stock, rice, mushrooms, onions and salt.
Simmer rapidly for 5 minutes.
Stir almonds into rice mixture and pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with browned chicken pieces.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Roll washed drummettes or wings in cornstarch.
Dip in egg. Fry in oil until golden brown.
Layer wings or drummettes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine all other ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until dressing sticks to the chicken and chicken is glazed.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: In large bowl cream together butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs; beat one at a time.
Blend in vanilla and milk.
Sift together flour, soda, powder, salt, cocoa and cinnamon and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add zucchini; stir well.
Turn into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle on top nuts and chocolate bits.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding directly from package evenly over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over bottom of pan.
Arrange rolls in pan leaving space between rolls for rising.
Combine melted margarine and brown sugar.
Pour over top of frozen rolls, the mixture will be very thick.
Place in cool oven overnight.
In morning after rolls have risen, bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until tops of rolls are brown.

title: white fudge
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan; brush sides of pan.

Add evaporated milk and sugar. Cook over medium high heat to boiling, about 8 minutes, whisking constantly to dissolve sugar. Cook an additional 12 minutes to soft-ball stage (236°). Remove from heat. Add chocolate, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla, nuts and cherries; stir until well blended.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. When firm, cut into 1-inch squares. Makes 117 pieces or about 4 pounds.

title: jello rainbow cake
directions: Line bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan with circle of aluminum foil.
Insert bottom into ring of pan.
Cut strip of wax paper to fit all around inside of ring and rising a bit higher than top. Stand wax paper all around inside of ring until paper meets. Scotch tape together.
Dissolve each package of gelatin separately using listed amounts of hot and cold water.
Place first bowl of Jell-O in refrigerator to thicken (not set).
When thickened, remove from fridge (put next bowl in fridge) and using electric mixer, beat until fluffy and about doubled in volume, then pour into the prepared spring-form pan.
Refrigerate; chill until firm but not set.
Repeat this procedure with each flavor allowing one to thicken, while one is being beaten.
When all favors are layered, place pan in fridge overnight to set.
Next day, remove outer ring first, then placing knife between paper and cake slowly remove wax paper.
Lift cake off pan bottom and place on serving plate.
Prepare one package of Dream Whip according to directions and frost cake.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: uncooked cranberry relish
directions: Core, but do not peel apples.
Take seeds out of orange (do not peel).
Grind all together and add sugar.
Let stand at least 12 hours to ripen before using.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, flour and milk.
Add beaten egg whites.
Add salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nutmeats and mix well.
Bake as a solid cake or in layers.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean or cake springs back when touched with finger.
Ice if desired.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with margarine over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat and blend in milk.
Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Combine coconut and nuts, sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° 45 minutes or until puffed.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Saute chicken and onions with thyme in melted oleo in large skillet until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch and stir until blended.
Stir in broth, milk, green beans, carrots, salt and pepper.
Bring to a full boil, stirring frequently.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serve.

title: wing dingers
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except chicken.
Add chicken wings; toss to coat well.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Place chicken wings and marinade in single layers in 15 x 12-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, cooking oil, powdered and white sugar. Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 35 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water in a large soup pot. Stir in chicken and cumin. Simmer over low heat for 2 hours.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar with Cool Whip.
Cap strawberries, cut in pieces; add glaze and set aside.
Cut cake in half; tear in small pieces.
Put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Add other 1/2 of cake.
Add berry mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lady bird johnson's pedernales river chili
directions: Place meat, onion and garlic in large heavy frypan or Dutch oven.
Cook until light colored.
Add oregano, cumin seed, chili powder, tomatoes, hot pepper sauce, salt and hot water.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer about 1 hour.
Skim off fat during cooking.

title: pumpkin chiffon
directions: Mix and press first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine and beat margarine, cream cheese, eggs and sugar until fluffy. Spread over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: streusel cream peach pie
directions: Place peaches in pastry lined pan. Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Beat together egg and cream.
Pour over peaches and sugar.
Mix the brown sugar, flour and butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve slightly warm with ice cream.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix powdered sugar, crackers and oleo and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Cool Whip, sugar and cream, cheese.
Spread on graham crackers.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: cracker jack popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 225° to 250°.
Pop corn (air popper is best). Set aside in large roaster or pan.
Mix butter, sugar and syrup in large pot.
Cook to a rolling boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla and baking soda; mixture will foam.
Pour over popcorn and mix until well coated.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every fifteen minutes.
Remove from pans and store in covered containers.

title: red hot pepper sauce
directions: In large glass bowl, combine peppers and boiling water.
Let stand 1 hour.
Heat oil and saute garlic, onion and spices for 3 minutes.
Remove peppers from water and run through food processor.
Return to water; add other ingredients and then place all ingredients in stainless steel pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours, adding water as necessary until towards the end when you get the final thickness desired. Remember the sauce will thicken a little when cold.
Place in refrigerator for storage.
It will keep 4 to 6 weeks.
You can also can it and water bath for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange salad(adapted from general foods kitchens cookbook)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Wash unpeeled orange; quarter, seed it and grind or food processor chop it with rind.
Fold cranberry sauce into gelatin, stirring to break up lumps.
Add ground orange, chopped apples and grapes.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Serve on crisp lettuce for 4 to 6.

title: cabbage mix
directions: Cut up cabbage, onion, celery and ham finely.
Steam with grated carrot, using very little water.
Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed on package.
Combine with cabbage mixture and add bouillon.
(Can be used as egg roll mix.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in margarine. Add soup, cheese, soy sauce, pepper sauce, salt and pepper. Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly.
Add beans and water chestnuts; mix thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with almonds. Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and mash with fork in medium bowl.
Stir in tomatoes, onion, juice, garlic powder and salt.
Refrigerate with the avocado seed in the mix (to keep guacamole from turning dark).

title: honey-applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, nonfat dry milk powder, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Set aside.

title: mango and lobster salad
directions: Prepare lobster by removing vein and sac near the head. Remove from shell and slice into 3-inch pieces.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of the lemon juice and set aside.
Peel and slice mangoes.
Place in a bowl with onions and chopped mint.
Mix the cream and lemon juice together and pour over the mangoes.
Add the lobster, season with the remaining lemon juice, salt and pepper. Serves 4 to 6.

title: green chile-pimento cheese
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a large bowl.
Yield:
about 6 cups.

title: seafood nachos
directions: Spread chips out on plate in single layer.
Layer crab meat, then cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave just until cheese melts, about 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Makes about 2 or 3 platefuls of nachos.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Season meat with garlic, onion and celery salt overnight in refrigerator.
Roast meat in baking pan at 275° for 1 hour per pound.
Cover meat with foil while baking.
Slice meat thin on the diagonal.
When done, mix remaining ingredients and pour over roast.

title: bit-o-honey
directions: Mix together (may have to mix with fingers).
Form into log on wax paper.
Chill and slice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls on large cookie sheet.
Pinch together and bake according to directions.
Cool.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill, garlic powder and onion.
Spread over cooled crescent pastry.
Top with onions, broccoli, cauliflower and green pepper.
Cut crust into large pieces.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry rice and chopped onion in butter until browned.
Add water, salt, pepper, stewed tomatoes with juice and chopped green pepper which is optional and mostly for looks.
Put on to cook (low) 30 minutes.
Do not remove lid while cooking.
When finished, if you desire it a little hotter, add juice from Ro-Tel.

title: zucchini quiche(very good)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch oblong Pyrex.
Mix dry ingredients together first, then add eggs and oil.
Then fold in the sliced zucchini, onions and parsley.
Mix well.
Spread in Pyrex.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
If not brown, turn on broiler until brown, but watch carefully.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a blender along with 1/4 cup of salad oil.
Mix well on medium low speed.
Slowly add remaining oil in a thin stream until mixture is thick and creamy.
Tastes great with carrots, celery, green pepper or any other vegetable.
Makes 2 cups.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O with the boiling water. Add the 7-Up. Refrigerate until thick. Stir in the pineapple and mandarin oranges. Refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate goober bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan. In a large bowl, combine cake mix, brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine at low speed until crumbly.
Add milk and egg; stir until blended.
Spread in prepared pan.
Sprinkle with peanuts. Press nuts into mixture.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion, egg and enough milk to form a stiff dough that will drop easily off a teaspoon.
Drop into deep, hot fat.
Cook until golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chewy-gooey cookies
directions: Cut margarine into dry cake mix.
Mix in 1 beaten egg.
You will have a crumbly mixture that will stick together with pressure.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: apple crunch
directions: Slice apples into medium baking dish, sprinkle with cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cream butter and rest of sugar.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to batter.
Batter will be thick, so spoon it onto the top of apples.
Bake 10 minutes at 425° then 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 15 servings.

title: tomatoes stuffed with chicken or tuna
directions: Wash tomatoes.
Remove thin slice from stem end of each. Scoop out pulp.
Save.
Sprinkle inside of tomatoes with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Invert tomatoes to drain 30 minutes.

title: italian beef sandwich
directions: Place beef in roasting pan, fill pan half full with water. Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and marjoram.
Lay sliced onion and carrots over roast.
Cover pan and roast meat in 350° oven for 3 to 5 hours.
Refrigerate roast in juice overnight.
Next day, slice roast thin, bring beef broth to a boil and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Carefully lay sliced beef in juice.
Spoon juice over beef.
Cover and heat in 350° until hot. Serve on buns or French bread.

title: chocolate strawberries
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave, then dip strawberries.
Put on cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator.
Takes about 20 to 30 minutes to harden.
Enjoy!

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Place meat in slow cooking pot.
Cover with sliced onion. Combine garlic, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika and mustard.
Stir in water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low for 9 to 10 hours.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve
the yeast in warm water.
Heat
milk,
sugar, salt and oil to lukewarm.
Add yeast and
of
the
flour; mix. Add egg and stir in remaining flour.
Cover and let rise 20 minutes.
Shape into rolls and let rise
again.
Bake
at 400° until brown.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about one minute; remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once.
Beat until smooth.
Drop dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake until puffed and golden, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool away from drafts.
Cut off tops and remove soft dough.
Fill with cream filling and replace tops; dust with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 6 cream puffs.

title: minced clam and cheese delight
directions: Melt margarine. Add flour.
Cook and blend.
Slowly add clams and juice.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk.
Stir to thicken.
Add cheese; heat until melted.
Serve over cooked pasta.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stir-fry pepper steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger; add beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.

title: tar heel pie
directions: Pour melted margarine over chocolate chips and stir.
Blend all remaining ingredients and stir into chocolate chip mixture. Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: e-z pound cake
directions: Mix sugar with cake mix. Mix well!

Slowly mix ingredients until well combined, then beat at regular speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tested done. Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Take out and glaze hot cake or cool and shake powdered sugar over cake.

title: date balls
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat thoroughly.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thick,
then
put 2 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla into
mixture and boil in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: tuna rolls
directions: Mix well. Shape into about 6 balls. Bake in oven at 500° for 5 minutes.
